title: easy grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar and salt, then stir in milk. Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Grease 2-quart baking dish and sprinkle with Grape-Nuts.
Add custard mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Dice carrots. Cook until tender, but not too soft. Make white sauce with the butter, flour and milk. Add onion, salt, pepper, mustard and cheese. Pour carrots into casserole. Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes. Gradually beat in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice. Stir together remaining ingredients. Fold into pumpkin mixture. Spread on a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Top with chopped nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar, then roll cake and towel together. Let cool about 5 minutes. Unroll and cool to touch.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine with onions and green pepper in a large bowl.
Stir together the remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate several hours or overnight. Drain, reserving marinade.
Serve as relish and return leftover vegetables to marinade until served again.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer sausage in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and other ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together except the strawberries and nuts.
Fold in the strawberries and nuts (if desired). Do not beat.
Put in cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Allow 20 to 25 minutes per pound.
If desired, rub meat with lemon juice before adding seasoning.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion.
Skim off grease. Melt cheese
separately, then add soup, taco sauce and garlic powder to the melted cheese.
Mix with meat.
Serve with taco chips.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon or salt pork until crisp.
Add onions.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and celery with seasonings.
Add water. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add chopped clams, liquid, then milk and butter.
Heat and thicken with cornstarch, if desired.
Stir constantly until creamy.
Enjoy!

title: real good pound cake
directions: Beat
everything
together
good.
Bake
in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes before removing from pan.

title: raspberry bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients; let stand 15 minutes.
Spread mixture in baking dish.

title: peach delight frosting
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Cut peaches into bite size pieces.
Mix yogurt and whipped topping; fold in peaches.
Fill layers of cake with half of mixture and spoon remaining mixture over top of cake. Refrigerate two hours before serving.
Works best with white cake.
Any flavor yogurt or fruit can be used.
For example, pina colada is heavenly!

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk until pudding is thick.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mix and mix together.
Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Layer bottom of dish with graham crackers, then pudding mixture.
Continue with alternate layers of graham crackers and pudding mixture.
End with a top layer of graham crackers.
Spread icing on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy chocolate roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Line 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan with foil.
Melt butter in pan; sprinkle nuts and coconut evenly in pan.
Drizzle with condensed milk.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup flour and powdered sugar.
Pat in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Stir granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Spread over crust.
Bake 25 minutes longer. Frost with powdered sugar and lemon juice frosting.
Cut in small squares.

title: enchilada casserole(microwave)
directions: Cook and crumble ground beef.
Add taco sauce, chili mix, refried beans and enchilada sauce.
Put ingredients in casserole dish.
Add taco shells or tortilla chips.
Cover with grated sharp cheese.
Bake in microwave or regular oven until cheese melts.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add milk and dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Set dough in refrigerator about 2 hours to chill.
Roll out on pastry sheet; cut and then deep fry.

title: dump cake #2
directions: Spread
pineapple
over
bottom
of a large 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Over pineapple, spread pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix
over pie
filling.
Pour melted oleo over cake mix.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: gingersnapscreston, iowa
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, shortening, egg and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients all at once, mixing well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and drop into plate of sugar.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until top cracks.

title: crunchy pudding
directions: Mix pecans and graham crackers with butter. Pat down like a pie crust in the bottom of pan. Mix pudding and Dream Whip as directions on boxes.
Spread chocolate evenly, then Dream Whip on top. Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Chill. Serve with boiled shrimp.

title: cool waldorf salad
directions: Mix just before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and nuts.
Cut each biscuit in fourths and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Layer 1/2 of the biscuits in bottom of greased tube pan.
(Bundt cake pan works well.)
Pour 1/2 of butter/brown sugar/nuts mixture over top. Layer remaining biscuits and top with last 1/2 of butter/brown sugar/nuts mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert on plate; pull apart to eat and enjoy!

title: shoya sauce marinade
directions: Mix together and marinate meat 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: mother's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and sugar.
Mix butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll on floured board thin and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
(You may sprinkle tops of cookies with sugar before baking.)

title: gingerbread kids
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Chill.
Roll between wax paper and cut with gingerbread man cookie cutters.
Use candy or raisins for eyes, buttons, etc.

title: baklava
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Separate 1 can of rolls into two long rectangles. Place into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up the sides; this forms the crust.
Spoon nut mixture evenly over dough.
Separate remaining can of dough into two long rectangles.
Place over nut mixture.
Press to edge of pan using dough edge and perforations as guidelines.
With sharp knife, score dough with 5 lengthwise and 7 diagonal marks to form 28 diamond shaped pieces.

title: lemon butter
directions: Beat eggs, juice and sugar.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened, stirring frequently.
Add butter and remove from stove.

title: steak and shrimp kabobs
directions: Arrange meat and vegetables on skewers.
Grill to desired doneness.
Serve on bed of rice or couscous and top with Bernaise sauce.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Fill a 3-quart saucepan with water and place over high heat. When water comes to a rapid boil, add salt and macaroni.
Cook, uncovered (according to directions on box), until tender.
Remove from stove.
Pour macaroni in colander to drain.

title: bread
directions: Heat sugar, salt, Crisco, milk and water until sugar dissolves, then cool.
Mix potatoes, eggs and dissolved yeast and add to cooled mixture.
Beat with mixer, knead in flour and raise until doubled (2 hours).

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water (no cold water). Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Fold in sour cream, crushed pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate until set.
Garnish with additional cherries, if desired.
(This is nice served in a glass bowl so all colors can be seen.) The texture can be varied by not thoroughly mixing the green Jell-O with the sour cream, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Add water, Bisquick and cheese.
Shape into small balls. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad #1
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice and sugar.
Add bananas, pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Freeze in cupcake liners in muffin pan.
After frozen, remove from muffin pan and place in a freezer container or freezer bags.

title: shaker village sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually and well beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Beat gently into butter/egg mixture.
Fold in egg whites and mix well.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Roll out and shape with cookie cutters or drop in tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: beef roll-up
directions: Spread a thin layer of garlic paste on meat.
Season with salt, pepper, parsley and grated cheese.
Add bread crumbs.
Roll up meat jelly roll style and secure with toothpicks.
Brown in oil and transfer to casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Add beef broth and wine to drippings.
Strain and pour over rolls.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 - 1 1/2 hr., depending on cut of meat.

title: captain's soup
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain excess fat.
Add undiluted soups and V-8 juice; blend.
Add vegetables, macaroni, salt and pepper. Let come to a boil, stirring often.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour, and salt in a bowl.
Stir in egg whites and extract.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased sheets.
Bake until brown.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Combine pineapple and blueberries with 1 cup sugar.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Melt butter.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Top with coconut and pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's sugar pie
directions: Make crust for 9-inch pie.
Put small pieces of butter in pie shell.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Beat in milk or half and half.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with skins on until soft.
Peel and put through food mill.
Add sugar, salt, melted butter and milk.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Pour in 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, putting marshmallows on top for last 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir with a spoon.
Put in a greased Bundt pan and bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Spoon into a greased and well floured pan. Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of batter into miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan; stir in 1 1/2 cups water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly and thickened.
Cook for 1 minute.
Stir half the hot mixture into egg yolks; blend egg yolks into hot mixture.
Cook for 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind; pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes or until meringue is light brown.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as slaw dressing or over lettuce.

title: aunt ruth's taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain fat. Add water and beef cubes and bring to a boil. Add cans of vegetables. DO NOT drain the cans. Add dressing and seasoning packages. Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, salt, almond and vanilla at high speed.
Gradually add sugar until mixture forms stiff peaks. Combine powdered sugar and flour.
Fold into mixture gradually. Put in ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool upside down.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix well.
Place in casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick of melted margarine.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: tuna bake with biscuits
directions: Melt shortening.
Add salt and flour and blend.
Then add soup and milk and cook until thick and creamy.
Add tuna and lemon juice.
Make 1 recipe of biscuits from Bisquick box.
Drop on the top of mixture.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 425° for 15 minutes.
The biscuits may be added after the first 15 minutes also.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice beef across the grain into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over beef. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Lay beef strips on rack.
Set over an aluminum foil-lined baking pan.
Prop oven open with pencil.
Bake 8 to 12 hours at 150°.

title: herb batter bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour, the yeast and fines herbes. Heat together the water, butter or margarine, sugar and salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring until butter almost melts. Add to yeast mixture.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Stir in remaining flour.
Cover; let rise until double.
Stir down dough.
Spread evenly in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover; let rise until double.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: blueberry poppy seed muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make well in center. Combine buttermilk and next four ingredients.
Add to flour. Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
After spooning into muffin pans, sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Contains 153 calories each.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; work in egg and molasses. Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Roll dough into walnut-sized balls.
Dip one side in sugar.
Place sugar side up on wax paper lined cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in large tube pan or Bundt pan.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix together flour, salt and soda and add to first mixture.
Add oats; stir in corn flakes (fold in).
Grease baking sheets and drop 3/4 teaspoon on sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes.
Test first to make sure; don't overbake.
Should be sort of chewy.
Makes about 17 dozen.

title: green bean, tomato and salami salad
directions: Cut salami into 2 x 1/4-inch thick sticks.
Put into mixing bowl.
Trim tips and ends of green beans.
Cut into 3-inch long pieces.
Steam for 10 minutes or until tender.
Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Mix ingredients of the dressing in a separate bowl with a whisk and then pour over the salad.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or more. Makes 4 servings.

title: oyster omelette
directions: Allow for every six large oysters or twelve small ones, one egg.
Remove the hard part and mince the rest very fine.
Take the yolks of eight eggs and the whites of four; beat until very light, then mix in the oysters.
Season and beat up thoroughly.
Put into a skillet a gill of butter, let it melt.
When the butter boils, skim it and turn in the omelette.
Stir until stiffens; fry light brown.
When the underside is brown, turn onto a hot platter.
To brown the upper side, hold a red-hot shovel over it.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, limeade, pudding and food coloring.
Pour in pie shell and put in refrigerator.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain and run cold water over them for 3 minutes.
Put in large bowl and add Ranch dressing and bacon bits.
Cut tomato and cucumber into cubes.
Add to mixture and refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well.
Cook in microwave oven on High until thickened, stirring about twice.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions for 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cool on wire rack.
Drain cherries, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Sprinkle over 1 cake layer.
Spread with pie filling.
Place remaining layer on top.
Spread whipping cream over top and sides.
Decorate with cherries.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix Duncan Hines cake mix, sour cream, sugar and cooking oil. Add eggs (beaten), one at a time.
Add 3 tablespoons of poppy seed and water.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine vanilla wafers and 3/4 cup melted butter.
Mix well and press onto bottom and sides of ???-inch pan or two 8-inch pans.
Combine confectioners sugar, soft butter and eggs.
Beat on high speed for 15 minutes. Do not overbeat.
Spread over crust. Top with sliced bananas. Cover with pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over fruit. Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill overnight. Cut in squares and serve. Serves 16 to 20 people.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: rachel's cheese cookies
directions: Mix cheese and butter.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add Tabasco and Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls.
Press on baking pan with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Makes 30.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Heat oil in 8-inch square baking pan until hot.
(Heated pan gives bread a crisp crust.)
Add eggs and buttermilk together to dry ingredients and mix lightly.
Add hot oil to batter and pour immediately into hot pan.
Bake 20 minutes or more until brown.

title: cheese blintz
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry in butter.
Top with sour cream and strawberry preserves.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops; set aside.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Put mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chops on top of potato mixture.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until browned.

title: broiled bass
directions: Soak fillets in 3 to 4 tablespoon salt to 2 quarts water overnight to rid bacteria and musky scent.
Double rinse fillets. Place on foiled cookie sheet.
Butter fillet tops with basting brush to moisten and baste with lemon juice to prevent drying out. Add Tiger sauce and black pepper.
Broil at 450°.
Have oven hot when you place fillets in oven.
Use fork to check tenderness. Fillet pieces will start to roll up and flake when tender.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Sift sugar, flour and baking powder together.
Add melted butter and milk; stir until well blended.
Divide mixture into 2 well-greased 9-inch pans.
Sprinkle tops with flour, then with brown sugar, then cinnamon.
Push chunks of butter into dough. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with silver spoon.
Beat in other ingredients until creamy.
(You can substitute 2 finely chopped green chili peppers instead of the chili powder.) Serves 4.

title: avgolemono
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat broth and rice to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
In small bowl with wire whisk or hand beater, beat eggs and lemon juice together until frothy.
Into egg mixture, stir small amount of hot broth; pour egg mixture into broth, stirring.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until soup is hot (do not boil).
Serve topped with lemon slices, if you wish.

title: split second cookies
directions: Put in bowl flour, baking powder and sugar.
Blend in butter, egg and vanilla.
Form into 4 rolls (3/4-inch thick, 13-inch long).
Place 4-inches apart on cookie sheet.
With knife handle, make dent down center of each roll.
Fill this dent with jelly or jam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, cut diagonally.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients except for spaghetti and cheese together in a large pot and heat over medium heat.
Add spaghetti, mixing well and pour in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and dish is heated through.

title: aunt max's hamburger dills
directions: Slice cucumbers into jars and fill with hot liquid.
Seal. Makes 3 to 4 quarts.
Pickles will be ready in 8 weeks.

title: wings
directions: Deep fry until crispy.
Add all ingredients to saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add wings until coated.
Remove from pan after coated.

title: hot casserole of crab meat(my standby for luncheons)
directions: Put 6 slices of bread in bottom of 13 x 17-inch casserole. Over this, put cheese and crab meat (be sure to remove scales, etc.).
Put 6 more slices of bread on top of this so that it looks like sandwiches.
Pour over this mixture the eggs, milk and salt. Let stand overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Sometimes needs 1 1/4 hours.
Serve cream of mushroom soup to which you have added fresh mushrooms as sauce over this.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces and put in bottom of pan.
Mix pudding separately.
Mix pudding and Dream Whip together.
Mix jello separately.
Pour pudding on top of cake pieces.
Put sliced strawberries on top of pudding.
Let jello start to jell and pour on top of strawberries.

title: strawberry stack cake
directions: Grease
and
flour
(9-inch)
cake
pans.
Pour
dry pudding mix into dry cake mix.
Mix according to directions on cake box to make a 3-layer cake.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cake cool completely.

title: mardelle's banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Whip whites and set aside. Add yolks to sugar and butter (fold in).
Dissolve soda into buttermilk. Fold into creamed ingredients.
Fold in flour, nuts, raisins and bananas.
Lastly, fold in egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes in loaf pan.

title: pecan party pies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Mix well and add vanilla and pecans.

title: crusty herb chicken
directions: Dip each breast half in buttermilk mixture and roll in crumbs. Place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cut up dates, large marshmallows and pecans with scissors dipped in hot water to keep them from sticking.
Gradually add graham cracker crumbs, saving 1 cup crumbs to roll in.
Squeeze all together with hands with plastic gloves on.
Gradually add cream and mix well.
Roll out on waxed paper with graham cracker crumbs, until 10-inch - 12-inch long.
Wrap in waxed paper and then kitchen towel to keep from drying out.
Slice and serve with cream whip on top.
Best if not cut for 12 hours.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Assemble all ingredients and utensils.
Combine in a bowl, flour, sugar, baking powder, milk and salt.
In a 2 quart baking dish, melt butter.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Toss peaches with 1 cup sugar and pour over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350 for 60 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Chop nuts; line bottom of pan with nuts and coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Spoon cake mixture (do not pour) on top of nuts and coconut.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Spoon cream cheese mixture on top of cake mix, alternating with the cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a bowl, combine buttermilk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Sift flour and soda into a large bowl. Stir in yeast mixture and mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out dough and cut into desired shape.
Butter the top and let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dip
directions: Chop the tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients in skillet.
Heat over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir constantly.
Keep warm.

title: zack's fish
directions: Fillet fish and lay flat in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Put onion over fish.
Put cheese over onion.
Put soup over cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Cut apples in half and core.
Place in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon and mix with water and pour over apples. Bake 1/2 hour at 350° or until soft.
Turn once to glaze if desired.
Serves 6.

title: nut rolls
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender. Beat the egg yolks with milk and crumble yeast into it.
Stir until dissolved, then add to the flour/shortening mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle sugar on pastry cloth and roll thin.
Cut into squares; spread filling on it.
Roll up and place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix as any cookie.
Divide into 2 loaves and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake the next day.

title: chicken livers stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Add chicken livers and mushrooms.
Season with paprika, salt, pepper and tarragon.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until livers are tender.
Add gravy and simmer for 10 minutes.
Slowly stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over rice and garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat in oil.
Add vegetables and stir-fry (until about 1/2 to 3/4 done).
Combine seasoning mix, soy sauce, sugar and water.
Add seasoning mixture.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Serve over rice. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: deep dish turkey with dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray two 1 3/4-cup casseroles with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In 1-quart saucepan, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add vegetables, stirring to coat with margarine.

Cover pan and cook over medium heat, until veggies are tender. Sprinkle veggies with flour and broth mixture and stir quickly to combine. Cook uncovered for 1 minute. Gradually stir in water and, stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add turkey and seasoning mix and stir to combine.
Pour half of mixture into each sprayed casserole.
Top each portion with 6 biscuit wedges and bake until thoroughly heated and "dumplings" are browned, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: best punch
directions: Thaw frozen juices and strawberries.
Combine all and drop sherbet on top.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients
in
order
given.
Roll in the size of walnuts and dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mott's magic apple roll
directions: Options:
Add
cup
heated jam to make a jelly apple roll. Use Mott's chunky applesauce.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring regularly to 236° (this takes a long time).

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, in blender. Cover and blend on low for 3 minutes. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together.
Add egg to mixture and mix well.
Mix entire ingredients together.
Chill and drop with spoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake until golden brown in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: sweet 'n' sour meatballs
directions: In a medium bowl, combine ground beef, onion, egg, mustard, salt, pepper and 2/3 cup (1/2 can) sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
Stir in crumbs.
Roll into 1-inch balls (meatballs will be soft).

title: pineapple-cottage cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a bubble boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool about 30 minutes.
Add cottage cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.
Stir gently.
Pour in long shallow dish (9 x 13-inch) and chill until firm.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and take off the bone.
In greased dish alternate layers of dressing mix, chicken and mushroom soup.
Repeat layer of dressing mix, chicken and 2 cans of chicken soup diluted with chicken broth.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or Pepperidge Farm dressing mix.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Stir by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: potato muffins
directions: Add milk to potatoes and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with potatoes and milk, then add beaten eggs. If potatoes are very dry, add a little more milk.
Add melted shortening last.
Bake in greased muffin tins in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes

title: apple salad
directions: Peel and cut apples into pieces.
Add crushed pineapple and mix with walnuts.

title: fruit delight
directions: Drain fruit. Mix eagle brand milk and lemon juice. Add all other ingredients. Stir. Refrigerate.
(This can be used as a fruit salad or as a desert. It is a wonderful dessert when served with a brownie).

title: meal on the grill
directions: Take a large sheet of aluminum foil, shape ground beef into patties (1 for each person) and layer on foil.
Cover with vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Seal foil and place on grill until done.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Saute the hamburger and garlic; drain off grease.
Add the next 5 items and simmer for 20 minutes.
While it simmers, cook noodles in boiling, salted water for about 15 minutes; drain them.
Fill a large buttered casserole dish with alternate layers of noodles, cheese, tomato meat sauce and Parmesan cheese, ending with a layer of sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: shrimp and crab mold
directions: Heat soup and stir in dissolved gelatine.
Add cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased mold; let set. Serve with crackers, etc.

title: millie's sugared nuts
directions: In a large frying pan, bring sugar and water to soft ball stage.
Remove pan from heat and immediately add cinnamon and nuts.
Toss until all liquid is absorbed.
Spread on waxed paper, working quickly to prevent nuts from sticking together.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: country blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir 1/2 cup sugar into fruit; set aside.
Melt butter in a baking pan.
Stir next 4 ingredients together; then add milk.
Pour batter into pan of melted butter. Do not mix.
Pour fruit over batter.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: squash soup
directions: Wrap the squash in foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Peel, seed and mash the squash.
Cook onions and cloves in stock until soft.
Remove cloves and add squash.
Puree in a blender. Cook curry powder in a little butter.
Add to the soup with the cream.
Blend. Let soup sit for about an hour to absorb the curry. Serve hot or cold.
If served cold, thin with a little light cream.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: easy fresh strawberry pie
directions: Clean and hull strawberries.
Cut strawberries into halves. Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons of water and set aside.
In saucepan, combine sugar and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add dissolved cornstarch.
Stirring constantly, cook until thickens and coats spoon.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberry Jell-O and cool to room temperature.
Pour strawberries into baked pie shell.
Cover with Jell-O mix and refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cover bottom of pan with chopped cabbage.
Cover with browned ground beef.
Over this, spread creamy mushroom soup.
Bake until cabbage is soft.

title: clam or conch chowder
directions: Clean and chop clams to desired size.
Add onions to clams. Cover with water (or clam juice), preferably clam juice, add fat drippings or cubed pork and cook 30 minutes or until tender.
Then add potatoes; let come to a boil.
Cook until potatoes are creamy. Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix ingredients in any order and amount desired.

title: oreo cookie torte
directions: Crush Oreos and save 3/4 cup for topping.
Melt butter and mix with cookie crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend 1 (12 ounce) Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup of powdered sugar together.
Spread over cookie mixture.
Mix pudding according to package.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread the other Cool Whip over the pudding and sprinkle with the cookie crumbs. Chill!!!

title: old english chip dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Good with Fritos corn chips.

title: "mock" chopped liver
directions: Cook string beans until crisp and tender.
Saute cubed or chopped onions in oil (fat).
Add mushrooms; saute, covered, until soft, then uncover and lightly brown.
Put walnuts, onions and mushrooms into food processor; blend until finely ground.
Remove. Add string beans.
Put defrosted Egg Beaters into pan; cook until firm.
Add to string beans; process until fine.
Mix all together. Season with salt and pepper.

title: barbecue burger
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and onion soup until thoroughly mixed.
Add sauce and mix well. Shape ingredients in several large patties.
Place patties into a cold large skillet.
Cook at low temperature.
Cover with lid when patties begin to sizzle and are lightly brown on underside.
Cook until done.

title: eggplant and rice fritters
directions: Combine eggplant with all ingredients except oil.
Mix well. Drop from spoon into 1/2-inch hot oil in skillet.
Fry until brown on each side.

title: famous fudge
directions: Put into saucepan sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Put into large bowl chocolate chips, marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Bring sugar, butter and milk to boil.
Cook 6 minutes (after full rolling boil).
Pour over dry ingredients and stir until mixed. Beat a few minutes.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into small squares.

title: paul newman's white chili
directions: Pick up the phone, dial 347-1111.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine beef and melted Spry.
Add onion, green pepper, carrot, crumbs, salt, paprika and mustard.
Blend.
Add tomato juice and mix well.
Pack in a baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2-inch, greased with Spry.
Spread ketchup on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: vegetable chili(10 servings)
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Chop green peppers and onion.
Cut zucchini and yellow squash lengthwise into quarters; cut each quarter crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook green peppers and onion until tender.
Add zucchini, squash, chili powder, sugar, salt and ground red pepper; cook for 1 minute.
Add stewed tomatoes with their liquid, pinto and black beans with their liquid, green chilies with their liquid and corn.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate-dipped shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Stir in 1 cup mini-morsels; mix well.
Drop dough by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets; shape into 2-inch logs or press into circles using bottom of floured glass.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Squeeze juice out of sauerkraut; add celery, pepper and onion. Combine sugar, oil and vinegar.
Toss well with sauerkraut mixture.
Marinate 24 hours.
Drain well and serve.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Put ground beef evenly in bottom of rectangular Pyrex dish. Salt meat to taste.
Put chopped onion over meat.
Place cheese slices over onions.
Slice potatoes over cheese and pour the soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix by hand; do not use electric mixer.
Sift first 5 ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients in small increments.
Add apples, walnuts and butterscotch chips.
(Note:
Mixture will be thick.)
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday spritz cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except flour.

With an electric mixer, beat at medium speed, 2 to 3 minutes, scraping bowl often, until mixture is light and fluffy. Add flour; beat at low speed, 2 to 3 minutes, scraping bowl often, until well mixed.
If dough is too soft, cover; refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes, until firm enough to form cookies.
Place dough into cookie press.
Form desired shapes 1-inch apart on cookie sheets. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: red skinned potato salad
directions: Toss together cooked cubed potatoes, celery, onions, peppers. In separate bowl blend mayo or salad dressing, milk, salts and seasonings.
Add sugar, vinegar, and whisk until smooth.
Pour over potatoes and gently mix until coated. Serve warm or chilled. Garnish with fresh parsley or sprinkle
with paprika. Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: aunt edna's shrimp dip
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill. Serve in a pretty dish with Ritz crackers.

title: vodka punch
directions: Makes 30 (5 ounce) servings when using 2 fifths vodka.

title: paul's hot slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate in air tight container. (This slaw has a long shelf life and is especially good with BBQ.)

title: cream cheese dream bars
directions: Mix by hand cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13 inch ungreased, glass pan.
Mix cream cheese and 2 eggs with electric mixer until smooth.
Add powdered sugar to the cream cheese/egg mixture.
Pour over cake mixture and bake in 325° oven for 65 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: In saucepan put milk, Grape-Nuts and maple syrup.
Heat until milk turns brown.
In bowl beat 4 eggs, sugar and salt.
Add to warm milk.
Pour into greased casserole.
Set in pan of hot water (halfway up dish).
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Place in ungreased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar peanuts
directions: Cook over medium heat until all moisture is gone (very dry). Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn every 15 minutes.
Add salt to taste.

title: diabetic - baked sweet potato
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat until smooth and creamy.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 1 serving.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix rhubarb, 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Put in bottom of large 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Make crumbly mixture out of remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Can sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg before baking.
Great served with vanilla ice cream.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the ground chuck with the onion, stirring until ground chuck is crumbly; drain well. In a large pot combine the ground chuck and onion with the salad dressing and taco seasoning mix. Add remaining ingredients (except cheese and sour cream) and mix well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours. Serve with cheese and sour cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, pepper, salt, Cheddar cheese, onion and 1/2 cup margarine.
Mix crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup margarine and place on top of potato mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
(Suitable for freezing.)

title: egg noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Brown hamburger and onions. Add soup
and mix.
Put in casserole dish, grate cheese on top and cook until cheese is melted at 350°.
Salt to taste.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and nutmeg in bowl or pan until soft like ice cream.
In separate bowl beat 6 or 7 eggs.
Add beaten eggs to mixture.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk and flour.
Chill dough before rolling out tea cakes.
Bake at 375°.

title: vegetarian roast
directions: Mix these ingredients and let stand a few minutes to allow bread crumbs to absorb moisture.
Add cup of tomato juice.
Add 2 or 3 eggs, well beaten.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and place in oiled ring mold pan.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
After dish cools somewhat, garnish with pimento, radishes and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry-orange punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, lemon juice and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add orange soda and liqueur; add ice.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix biscuit mix and cheese.
Add water and sausage and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
Mix and stir in sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with a lattice top. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.

title: taco hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; set aside.
Cook macaroni and drain; stir in all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Pour into a large casserole dish and top with cheese; crumble chips on top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil together sugar, milk, syrup.
Boil to a soft ball that forms in a cup of cold water.
Take off heat then stir in butter and peanut butter.
Beat until thick, then pour in a pan.
Let cool; cut.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and carrots 5 minutes and drain.
Mix dressing as directed.
Fold in zucchini, onion and carrots with sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Put dressing in bottom (save 1/3 for top).
Place sliced chicken on top of dressing, then zucchini mixture, then dressing on top.
Salt and season to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lola's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix. Put in pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: After cooking and mashing squash, add half of butter, onion, crumbled saltines, sugar, salt and pepper and mix well.
Coarsely grate (or cut into chunks) cheese and add to squash mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish and crumble Ritz crackers and oleo over top.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Fifteen minutes before removing from oven, spread the topping over the top and continue baking.

title: bessie's oriental chicken wings
directions: Boil all ingredients for 30 minutes.
Drain and place on cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scallop corn
directions: Mix well. Turn into 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skeeter's pie crust
directions: Place the first 8 ingredients in a large pan and bring slowly to a boil for 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Add dry ingredients to wet and stir to blend.
Stir in vanilla flavoring. Pour into greased and floured large Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese and honey mixture, if desired.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a full boil.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add to boiled mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Let stand until hard.

title: starburst salad
directions: Arrange lettuce wedges in salad bowl.
Combine carrots, zucchini, mushrooms and olives.
Toss lightly.
Place over lettuce wedges.
Chill. Combine sour cream and dressing, mixing until blended.
Serve with salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Cut each of the 4 cans of biscuits into quarters.
Shake in sugar/cinnamon mixture to coat.
Place in greased Bundt pan, sprinkle with chopped walnuts. Melt butter and stir in brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits in pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ham. Spread mixture on ham slices; roll and secure with toothpicks. Refrigerate several hours; slice and serve with toothpicks.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer each of the ingredients in order into a large bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix flour and grated cheese.
Add salt and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Add melted butter and Tabasco.
Roll out into small balls. Press with fork.
Cook on 400° until done.

title: american-fried potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, add potatoes to hot bacon drippings or oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Turn potatoes and cook, uncovered, over medium-high for 5 minutes, loosening once or twice.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir every minute, then cook 2 more minutes without stirring.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda immediately after taking from microwave.
Covers approximately 2 quarts popped corn.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Mix soup and water together; set aside.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Place cheese on top of chicken.
Spread soup mixture on cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until bubbling.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cover and sear pork chops in hot skillet. Add all ingredients. Cover tightly and cook on low temperature until chops are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: jello salad 2
directions: Bring to boil pineapple and jello.
Remove from heat and add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Chill overnight.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Freeze on cookie sheets, then put into plastic bags to store in freezer until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Let cheese and sausage come to room temperature.
Mix together and shape into small balls.
Place on large cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 36.
May be stored in refrigerator before baking.

title: kluski z kapusta po polski(polish noodles and cabbage)
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onions; saute until soft. Add cabbage and saute 5 minutes or until crisp-tender; stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, cook noodles in salted, boiling water as directed on package; drain well.
Stir noodles into cabbage; add sour cream, if desired.
Cook 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.
Beat cream cheese in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until ready to serve.

title: mexican-style quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes. Lower heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour; add milk.
Cook to thicken.
Stir in cheese.
Combine sauce, tuna and noodles.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In large Pyrex baking dish, mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Place chicken breasts in mixture and turn to coat. Top with crushed crackers soaked in melted margarine.
Sprinkle generously with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Put all first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl and mix.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Then add 1/3 cup sour milk and 2/3 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in an oblong cake pan.

title: roux
directions: Cover bottom of heavy pot with olive oil.
After the olive oil is well heated over a slow fire, add the flour.
Cook the flour very slowly, stirring almost constantly. The flour must be browned to a very dark brown, nearly black, but not actually burned.

title: reuben roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out dough to approximately 36 x 7-inch.
Combine sauerkraut, Swiss cheese, corned beef and dressing.
Spread mixture down center strip (lengthwise).

title: spiced nuts
directions: Add water to egg white.
Dissolve sugar in egg white mixture. Add salt and spices and mix well.
Add nuts and stir well.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in slow oven at 250° until golden brown, about 1 hour.
Stir a few times to coat nuts evenly.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a pan. Bring to a boil over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well, then add oats.
Stir until thickens. Drop on wax paper.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.

Layer ingredients in order listed using dry cake mix in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish or pan. Bake 60 minutes. Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving. Serve warm or cool and if desired, with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes approximately 12 to 15 servings.

title: hearty hodgepodge
directions: In a large pan, cook beef, onion, celery and garlic.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vivian's famous buttermilk pie
directions: In a bowl, mix flour and sugar together. Add eggs and mix well. Add melted margarine, buttermilk and flavorings. Mix all ingredients well.

title: new england turkey chowder
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, saute celery and onion in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes over medium-high heat until tender and crisp.
Add broth, potatoes, salt, cayenne and pepper.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to low when mixture is at a simmer.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in turkey.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to the first mixture.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl.
Add to butter; blend.
Bake in three 9 or 10-inch pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Cover with Red Velvet Icing.

title: refried beans
directions: Mix well, continue cooking, stirring frequently until beans are thickened and butter is absorbed. Serve at once or refrigerate for later use. (I put 1 to 2 c. in freezer containers and freeze for later use.) I also find the crock pot works well to put beans in after they are mashed. Cook on low for the remainder of time.

title: toddler fun mix
directions: Mix raisins, grapes and marshmallows together and place in middle of plate.
Place broken graham crackers around fruit mix and watch for big toddler smile!
Serve with milk.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain off grease.

Stir in can of soup. Stir in prepared macaroni and cheese (per box directions). Heat through, either in microwave on High for 5 minutes (stir about half way through) or in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Bring sugar and pineapple to a boil.
Add cream cheese, jello, water, nuts and celery.
Chill, then whip small can Carnation milk; fold in mixture.
Chill.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: ruth's pepperkocker
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Roll small amount at a time to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface and cut into circles or roll into small balls and flatten to 1/4-inch with the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 360° for 10 minutes. Dough can be frozen and baked later.

title: maw-in-law helen's fried squash dressing
directions: Fry bacon; remove and crumble.
Dip squash in milk; dredge in Mexican meal.
Fry in bacon drippings until golden.
Add crumbled bacon; cover and remove from heat.
Steam will soften to a loose dressing texture.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Measure 1 cup of cake mix and set aside for topping.
Mix remaining cake mix with margarine and 1 egg.
Put into 9 x 13 inch greased and floured pan.
Mix pumpkin pie mix, 3 eggs, milk, cinnamon and sugar.
Pour over cake batter.

title: meringue mint cookies
directions: Mix egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Stir in food coloring and chips.
Drop on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off and put cookies in.
Leave in overnight.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Combine turkeyburger, onion, pepper and mushrooms in pan. Cook on medium heat until brown.
Drain and add sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: sweet icicle pickles
directions: Put cucumber strips in stone jar or stainless steel container. Add salt to water and bring to boiling.
Pour over cucumbers. Cover with dinner plate or glass pie plate.
Fill Ball jar with water and use to hold plate under brine.
Cover and let stand 1 week in a cool place.
If scum forms, remove it each day.
Drain, discarding brine.
Rinse cucumbers thoroughly.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours; drain.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boiling.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cover and let stand 24 hours.
Drain syrup.
Bring syrup to boiling and pour over cucumbers.
Repeat this step each day for 4 days.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt together into bowl. Add vinegar, oil and cold water.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla; beat for 1 minute.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and top with Wacky Cake Topping.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together; spread a layer on bottom of casserole dish.
Spread a large spoonful into each tortilla and roll up.
Arrange in dish, one at a time.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese chicken turnovers
directions: Place 1 slice of Prosciutto or smoked ham and 1 slice of cheese on each flattened chicken breast.
Fold in half.
Secure with wooden toothpicks or small skewers.
In a large frying pan, heat oil and butter over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 4 to 5 minutes per side.
Add wine and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove to a serving platter, discard picks.
Garnish with parsley.
Very good and easy.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine salt, sugar, dry mustard, pepper, garlic, lemon juice, water, oil and onion in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake until thoroughly blended.
Chill.

title: chocolate lust
directions: Combine flour, butter and pecans into pastry dough.
Spread into glass baking dish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.
Cream together softened cream cheese and sugar.
Fold Cool Whip into creamed mixture.
Spread on cooled baked crust.
Mix pudding and milk as directed on pudding box.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil the eggs for 10 minutes. Remove shells and cut eggs in halves.
Remove the yolks and put into a medium size bowl.
Use a chopper and break egg yolks until they are very fine.
Add mayonnaise, a little at a time, mixing with a fork.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
The parsley flakes are mostly for color so add as little or as much as you want.
Your texture may now seem dry.
Add a little milk at a time until the mixture is creamy, not too dry.
Using a teaspoon, start filling the eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Add squash and vanilla.
Mix together flour and cinnamon and add to moist ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Mix 7-Up and red hots in saucepan over medium heat until candy dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Stir and let sit until cool.
Add applesauce and stir well.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until chilled and firm.

title: vegetable barley soup
directions: Heat oil in 4 to 5-quart pot over medium high heat.
Add onions, carrots, celery and garlic powder.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are barely tender.
Add water, tomatoes, beans, barley, basil, bouillon cubes and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until barley is barely tender.
Add frozen kale.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes longer, stirring once or twice to break up kale, until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Just before serving, stir cheese into soup.

title: basic sauce for wok stir-fry
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Blend in water, soy sauce and sherry.
Use on meat and/or vegetable combination.

title: cherry crumble
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, baking soda and oats.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Mix and spread (all but 3/4 cup of mixture) in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Press down.
Spread cherry pie filling over crust, then sprinkle 3/4 cup of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey crescent wreath
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 9 ingredients. Coat a 14-inch pizza pan with nonstick cooking spray. Separate crescent dough into 16 triangles. Place wide end of 1 triangle 3-inches from edge of prepared pan with point overhanging edge of pan. Repeat with remaining triangles along outer edge of pan, overlapping the wide ends (dough will look like a sun when complete). Lightly press wide ends together. Spoon turkey mixture over the wide ends of dough. Fold the points of the triangles over the filling and tuck under wide ends (filling will be visible). Brush with egg white. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 16 servings.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown and let cool onion and hamburger.
When cool, mix in tomato sauce, garlic powder, salt, pepper and Mozzarella cheese. Spoon mixture onto hamburger bun half.
Sprinkle lightly with oregano.
Put top half of bun on filling and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 10 to 15.
Freezes well.

title: sour cream biscuits*
directions: Mix Bisquick and sour cream.
Add 7-Up gradually until right consistency.
Either drop on baking pan sprayed with Pam or pat into biscuit with hands (floured).
Spray on top with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: b. l. t. dip
directions: Mix all together the night before serving. Serve with Fritos, Hi-Ho crackers or anything.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon and pour into flat pan.
Bake with bacon on top for one hour at 375°.

title: baked bean too
directions: Rinse beans, then soak overnight.
Drain.
Place beans in a bean pot or deep baking dish with the molasses, onions, brown sugar, dry mustard and bacon.
Bake slowly at 225° for 4 hours.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Sift dry ingredients together. Add 1/2 of grated cheese to Crisco, and mix well then cut the shortening into the dry ingredients. Mix everything in until it becomes coarse. Add buttermilk, and mix until it becomes uniform. Drop biscuits into greased muffin tins. This will make about 12 or so. When you have completed this, sprinkle the rest of the cheese, a little extra garlic powder, and some dried parsley on the biscuits. Bake for 12 - 15 minutes. When done remove from oven, and brush on a little butter. Serve while still warm.

title: bruschetta
directions: Brush both sides of bread slices with olive oil.
Put on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle one side with garlic salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Broil for 2 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in four pieces.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and shake biscuit pieces in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Oil a tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Combine 1 cup sugar with margarine and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and pour over biscuits placed in the pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Let stand 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, bread crumbs, salt and milk.
Shape into balls and brown in oven at 375° for approximately 15 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and heat on stove.
Add slices of pepper.
Add meat balls to saucepan and simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: pfeffernuss cookies
directions: Beat egg, egg yolks, vanilla and salt.
Add brown sugar.
Beat with a spoon until thick.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and pepper.
Add citron or candied lemon peel.
Stir until mixture is smooth and mixed well.
Chill.
Form into small balls between the palms of your hands, 3/4-inch thick.
Bake on cookie sheet in 375° oven for about 8 minutes.
When baked, put into bag in which powdered sugar has been placed.
Shake for a minute.

title: healthy easy meat loaf
directions: Mix well and shape into loaf.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Shape into small, 1 inch balls. Roll balls in chopped walnuts.
Serve on cocktail picks.

title: pizza spaghetti hot dish
directions: Mix noodles, pizza sauce and ground beef.
Put half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then a single layer of pepperoni; then half the cheese.
Repeat layer, bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serves 8-10 people.

title: mexican (taco) salad
directions: Brown the hamburg. Drain grease and add the taco seasoning according to directions (as if you were making tacos).
While hamburg is simmering, chop the lettuce, onion, tomatoes and avocado.
Put in a very large pan (I recommend something along the size of a small lobster pot).
Add to this the beans, cheese and chips.
Add the cooked hamburg that has been simmering in the taco seasoning.
Finally add the salad dressing. Mix all of the ingredients and serve immediately. Serve with sour cream, salsa, extra taco chips and extra grated cheese.
Can be eaten cold the next day or heated in the microwave; only remember that the taco chips will not be "crunchy."

title: mr ranch pot roast
directions: Place roast on heavy foil. Sprinkle soup over meat and wrap. Place in a 200° oven at 9 a.m.
Remove at 5:30 p.m.
and it is ready to eat.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Brown onion and bacon; pour off 3/4 grease.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and mustard.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Drain all beans, but pork and beans, and mix.
Pour bacon mixture over bean mixture and stir.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix and place on ungreased cookie sheet with spoon. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Cool 1 minute and serve.

title: almond bark bars
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler over hot water.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Put in buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cut in squares when cool or drop by spoonfuls into clusters.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening and peanut butter; mix well.
Gradually add both sugars; cream thoroughly.
Add egg and milk; mix well.
Sift together salt, soda and flour, then add to other mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Press lightly with a floured fork one way, then the opposite way.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let stand until cool.
Add soda to dates; add all together and bake at 350°.
When cool, break into pieces and use Dream Whip to blend together into large bowl. Decorate top with candied fruit if desired.
Better if stands overnight.

title: tempura vegetables(batter fried vegetables)
directions: Beat
egg yolks with water;
when smooth, sift in flour gradually,	stirring as well.
Stir only until combined.
Heat oil to
approximately	325°
to 350° in temperature.
Dip the ingredients (fruits or vegetables) in the batter and carefully drop
them	into the oil.
Fry until brown and puffy and risen to the surface.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately or keep warm in a 300° oven on a tray in a single layer.

title: vanilla pudding salad
directions: Cook pudding and cool.
Add other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with bananas. Top with blueberry pie filling. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: aunt kay kay's puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes in microwave.
Stir it and mix well.
Then pour these ingredients over 4 1/2 cups Rice Chex cereal.
Mix well.
Pour into paper bag and shake 1 cup powdered sugar over cereal mixture.
Shake well or until covered. Sit back and watch the kids enjoy!

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Set aside.

Bring to a boil one stick oleo, Crisco, water and cocoa. Add eggs and buttermilk with soda and vanilla mixture (beat buttermilk, soda and vanilla together before adding to eggs). Pour over dry mixture and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Put all ingredients in punch bowl and serve chilled.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine; cool.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla. Beat well and add baking powder, flour, soda, oatmeal, cornflakes, pecans and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet with an ice cream scoop (2 to 3 per cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon logs
directions: Cream butter, sugar, cinnamon and almond extract in a mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour; beat well.
Cover and chill until firm.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch logs.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Dip in confectioners sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: swedish baked rice and carrots
directions: Bring rice and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand covered about 10 minutes.
Grate carrots and simmer until partially cooked.

title: surprisingly good broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain onion and broccoli (adding 1/2 teaspoon of salt to cooking water). Place broccoli mixture in large mixing bowl and add cheese, soup and mayonnaise. Spread into 9 x 13 baking dish that has been greased. Sprinkle dressing mix on top of broccoli and dot all over with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: biscuits for shortcake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Cut the shortening into the mixture.
Mix the beaten egg and milk together; add to the crumbly mixture.
Just stir lightly; don't beat.
Turn out on a floured board.
Roll out to 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Cut out and cook in a hot oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chili roasted turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In small bowl, blend all ingredients except turkey. Let stand 5 minutes. In roasting pan, place turkey, breast side up. Brush soup mixture onto turkey; tent with aluminum foil. Roast 1 hour, basting once. Remove foil and continue roasting 1 hour or until meat thermometer reaches 175°. Let stand, tented with aluminum foil,
10 minutes. Makes about 6 servings.

title: lo-cal cocoa
directions: Combine the dry milk and cocoa.
This can be stored at room temperature.
Fill a mug with 3/4 cup water.
Microwave water on High for 1 minute, or until hot.
Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa mix and 1/2 to 1 packet of Equal.
This makes 4 cups of cocoa.

title: strawberries (candy)
directions: Mix Jello, milk and coconut together.
Shape into a strawberry and roll in red sugar.
Dip end into green sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until not quite done.
Grate potatoes. Combine with sour cream, soup and melted butter.
Grate cheese and dice onions.
Combine with rest.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and tapioca; add salt and cinnamon.
Add these ingredients to berries.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Mix margarine, sugar and lemon juice and dot on top of berries.
Add top crust and bake at 350° until brown (about 30 minutes).

title: italian beef stir-fry
directions: Stir garlic in oil in large skillet over medium heat 1 minute or until done.
Add beef strips.
Season with salt and pepper and cook until done.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add zucchini; stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Return beef to skillet with tomato halves and dressing.
Heat through.
Serve over hot pasta; sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: french pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Heat frypan.
Brush with a little butter or oil.
Pour in enough batter to cover the bottom.
Tip the pan to make sure batter is even and thin.
Brown on one side. When top is set, turn pancake.
When done, butter, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Or put in jelly and roll jelly roll fashion.
Or roll and put on syrup.
Kids love these.

title: lizzies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add bourbon and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients (reserving 1/2 cup flour for fruit) and blend.
Cut up fruit and mix with the 1/2 cup flour before adding with nuts to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 12 minutes.

title: pineapple candied yams
directions: Drain yams, saving 1/2 cup syrup.
Arrange yams in baking dish. Mix the 1/2 cup syrup, pineapple, honey, sugars, nutmeg and raisins.
Bring to a boil and slowly add flour that has been mixed with water.
Cook until mixture thickens slightly.
Pour mixture over yams.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Set dish on cookie sheet in case of boil over.
The last 5 minutes of baking time, cover yams with marshmallows. Bake until brown.

title: gourmet potato soup
directions: In saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes. Add 1 cup milk; heat through. In medium bowl, blend sour cream and flour; gradually stir in remaining 1 cup milk. Pour about 1/3 of hot mixture into sour cream mixture. Return to pan.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add dried chives as needed.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt margarine, mix sugar and let cool.
Add egg and vanilla. Mix flour with nuts and add to sugar mixture.
Pour in greased pan and sprinkle top with chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 brownies.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 6 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour; add juice, cheese, carrots and pineapple.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine margarine and crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered. Very colorful in a glass dish (fall colors for Thanksgiving).

title: overnight french toast
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place bread on greased rimmed baking sheet.
Slowly pour batter over bread; turn bread until it is coated on both sides.
Cover with waxed paper, pressed onto bread. Refrigerate overnight.
Melt butter in skillet and fry bread until golden brown on both sides or bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Do not turn in oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.
Remove waxed paper before baking.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and cream alternating until you use all.	Add vanilla. Pour into large tube pan well-greased.
Bake at 325° for
hour and 20 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake is done.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix all together minus 1/2 can tomato paste.
Put meat mixture in aluminum foil.
Cover with remaining tomato paste.
Wrap loose. Put in crock-pot on high for 4 hours or 6 hours on low.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and reserve chunks and juice separately.
In a medium saucepan, cook sugar, egg yolks, flour and pineapple juice over medium heat until mixture is thickened. Remove from heat and add margarine.
Stir until blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: marjorie boyd's baked zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Brown onion in salad oil; add tomatoes.
Place half the zucchini in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Add half the tomato mixture; add half the bread crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(I added shredded sharp cheese.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients and congeal to soft stage.
Then use a fork and swirl sour cream through top of jello to marbleize.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over very low heat. Stir until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in condensed milk, butter and vanilla. Blend until butter is mixed with the chocolate.
Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture immediately into a lightly oiled 8-inch square pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into even squares. Yields 1 1/4 pounds.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems; save stems for filling. Place caps, hollow side up, in shallow baking dish or pie plate. Arrange larger ones to outside and smaller ones inside.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Thin the cheese with milk.
Add next four ingredients and place in an 8-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Brown pecans in butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers (looks like a pie).

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs until thoroughly blended.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Stir in carrots, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: marinated zucchini
directions: Mix together the cider vinegar, wine vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool and then add salad oil.
Into a large glass bowl or casserole, slice the zucchini, celery and bell peppers.
Separate the onion slices. Cover with sauce; put on cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and baking soda.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. (Dough will be stiff.)

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mash the potatoes and add the margarine and the cheese which has been cut in pieces.
Whip until very smooth.
Drizzle Pet milk and beat until very smooth again.
Fold in a desired amount of onion flakes.
Spray a casserole dish and pile the potatoes in. Top with a little grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove and bring to room temperature and then bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Very good!

title: soojeonggwa(cinnamon and ginger tea)
directions: In a large Dutch pan put together the water, cinnamon and ginger.
Boil and simmer for 2 hours.
Melt the brown sugar in the hot water with cinnamon and ginger.
Heat and boil again for 30 minutes.
Cool it down and chill.
Serve with 5 or 6 pine nuts.

title: wartime molasses cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll and cut about 15 large cookies.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: iowa steak soup
directions: Brown meat in oil; cook onion, carrots and celery in 8 cups of water. Add bouillon cubes, meat and garlic powder. Mix butter and flour with 1 cup liquid. Add and cook, stirring until bubbling. Add remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice. Cream together the sugar, oil, eggs and buttermilk. Add dry ingredients. Add the nuts, prunes and vanilla. Mix together and pour in greased and floured pan. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend well and store in refrigerator.
Keeps for 2 months. Great with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: apple pie(diet)
directions: Sprinkle bread with cinnamon and Brown Sugar Twin.
Slice apple into thin slices.
Cover bread with apple slices.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon and Brown Sugar Twin on top of apples and add 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, oleo and chocolate chips; pour over cereal and mix.
Place cereal and powdered sugar in large bag and shake until cereal mixture is covered.

title: herbed pot roast with vegetables
directions: Trim excess fat from roast if necessary.
Rub Dutch oven with fat.
Cook beef over medium heat until brown.
Sprinkle with herbs; add cider and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables, parsley and if necessary, 1/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until vegetables and beef are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Combine gelatin and hot water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in softened cranberry sauce.
Add walnuts and pineapple.
Pour into mold and let set overnight.

title: good luck black-eyed pea soup(men love it!)
directions: Rinse peas.
Place in large soup kettle and cover with water. Place lid on kettle and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer 2 minutes.
Set aside, tightly covered, for a minimum of 1 hour.
Can leave for 3 to 4 hours.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all and put in covered bowl.
Does not need to rise before baking, but better if it sits overnight.
Bake at 350°.
Keep unused dough in refrigerator.
Use 2 packages of yeast if you like it yeasty.

title: fresh apple cake
