directions: Beat sugar, eggs, flour, oil, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla until well blended. Add apples, raisins and pecans. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 10-inch tube cake pan with cooking spray.
Mix cake mix, cream cheese, water, eggs, egg whites, lemon zest, lemon juice, and poppy seeds together with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds to moisten.
Increase speed to medium and blend well- about 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan, and bake about 40 minutes until done.
Cool in pan on rack for 20 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and cool completely. Prepare glaze by stirring together sugar and lemon juice until mixture forms a smooth thick glaze.
Spoon over cooled cake, let drip down sides. Makes 18 servings.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Combine dry cake mix, coconut and cinnamon; stir in butter. Press 2/3 of mixture into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with pie filling.
Crumble remaining coconut mixture on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yummy punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add sugar, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Add water to make almost a gallon or to taste. Chill until slushy (in freezer).

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Mix together and simmer for 5 minutes. Serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix; roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
You may freeze them and reheat at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: 5 hour (no peek) stew
directions: In large Dutch oven layer all ingredients except tapioca or cornstarch, salt
and
pepper.
Combine
tapioca,
salt
and pepper and sprinkle over stew;
cover.
Bake in 250° oven for 5 hours.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: speedy pizza
directions: Step 1:
Place crescent roll dough on an ungreased cookie sheet; unroll and flatten to approximately 10 to 14 inches. Press together to seal.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift into 9 x 9-inch pan the first 5 ingredients.
Add vanilla, oil and vinegar.
Add water to mixture.
Blend well. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Blend butter and sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in apples, bran cereal and sifted dry ingredients.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. When cool, spread with frosting.

title: cream of broccoli soup with ham
directions: Cook vegetables 10 to 12 minutes in enough water to cook completely.
Add can of evaporated milk, cream of broccoli soup, 1 1/2 cans water, bouillon cubes, Mrs. Dash, potato flakes, salt, pepper and 1 cup finely chopped ham or can of Hormel ham.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, adding more water if needed.
Soup should be thick and creamy.
Add 1/8 teaspoon coriander while soup simmers. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash and pick lentils. Soak overnight in 2 cups water.

In Dutch oven or soup kettle, saute onion, garlic, carrots and celery in oil. Add lentils, 6 cups water, pepper, tomato paste, bay leaves and oregano. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until lentils are soft. (Add more water if necessary.) Remove bay leaves. Add vinegar and serve. Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together onion, celery soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese. Add broccoli, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add melted margarine.
Add Ritz crackers as topping.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cayenne cheese surprises
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Watch carefully and cool before removing from cookie sheet.
They can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine
eggs,	sugar
and
oil in a large mixing bowl; beat well.
Combine
flour,
soda, salt and cinnamon;
add to sugar mixture and beat well.
Stir in carrots, pecans, pineapple	and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at	350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick
inserted in	center	comes
out
clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook
macaroni	in
boiling
salt
water
until tender. Drain. Add
margarine, pepper, bread crumbs, milk and cheese. Bake in casserole about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ratatouille nicoise
directions: Pour olive oil in heavy pan and brown eggplant, onion and squash together until soft.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until well cooked, approximately 2 hours.
Serve hot or cold.

title: light and easy torte
directions: Frost with Cool Whip and top with Heath bars or Bits 'O Brickle.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli
directions: Melt butter; saute onion.
Blend seasoning, flour, bouillon cube and milk.
Cook to boil.
Add cheese and broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pear salad or pineapple salad
directions: Place pear or pineapple on a bed of lettuce. Fill fruit cavity with mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise and nuts. Place cherries on top.

title: butterscotch apple treat
directions: In a large bowl combine apples, marshmallows, peanuts, pineapple and raisins.
Combine whipped topping and dry pudding mix; fold into fruit mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate until serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Add can of coconut.

title: victory garden casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 3 or 4-quart casserole.
Drain all canned vegetables or, if using fresh, pre-cook until almost tender.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in 1 unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve 1/10 of a piece as this is a rich dessert.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together in a small saucepan.
Boil 1 minute after it comes to complete boil.
Cool and add 2 teaspoons vanilla; beat and put on cake.

title: camphouse rice
directions: Chop onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and water; bring to a boil.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Drain the peaches:set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, butter, egg, milk, and pudding for 2 min.

title: apricot cheesecake
directions: Simmer the apricots in water for 30 minutes, then drain. Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Toss the gingersnap crumbs with the melted butter in small mixing bowl. Press crumbs over the bottom and 1-inch up the side.
Puree the apricots with the orange zest in food processor fitted with the steel blade.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in large mixing bowl until smooth.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Gently fold in sour cream and apricot puree until completely blended.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake until center is firm, 50 to 60 minutes. Cool on wire rack, then refrigerate until chilled.
Top with fruit, if desired.

title: penuche coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until thoroughly blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add and blend thoroughly.
Stir in coconut.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add nuts if you like.
Put this batter in a large baking dish.
Bring to boil remaining ingredients and pour over batter.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: egg-cheese bake
directions: Spread margarine over 1 side of each slice of bread.
Cut each slice diagonally into 4 triangles.
Cook and stir onion in 1 tablespoon margarine until onion is tender.
Spread mixture in oblong baking dish (12 x 7 1/2-inch) square or 9 x 9 x 2-inch. Top with egg slices and sprinkle with cheese.

title: glaze for fruit pies
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch; cook until clear.
Add jello and lemon juice.
Cool slightly and pour slowly over fruit. Makes enough for 2 pies.

title: baked beans
directions: Put the pork and beans in a roaster.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together; add some of the bacon grease. Bake for 2 to 3 hours at 300°.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat.
Marinade meat for at least 24 hours.
Grill as desired.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill

a large pot with water. Add the Old Bay seasoning. Bring to a boil. Add the potatoes and return to boil and cook for 10 minutes. Add sausage and corn. Return to boil and cook for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes (turn pink).
Remove from heat. Serve with French bread, cole slaw or salad.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Dump all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Since ovens vary, top should be tested with a toothpick until it comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
This freezes very well.

title: rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt and eggs until well blended. Add 2 cups hot water and mix well. Add yeast to mixture and stir. Gradually add flour; cover mixture with a cup towel and refrigerate overnight.

title: caramels from the "globe"
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, butter and half and half over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until 240° or candy forms a solid ball in cold water.
Take off heat; add vanilla and pour into well buttered dish.

title: miss mary's famous chicken with pastry
directions: Place chicken in 3 cups water with onion, celery and salt. Cook until tender over medium heat.
When tender, remove chicken from broth and debone.
Cut into large chunks and place in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Remove celery and onion from broth.
Blend flour with cold water and gradually whisk until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour enough sauce over chicken to cover.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine 2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Sprinkle with water.
Mix until it holds together and forms a ball.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into strips and place over chicken.
Bake until pastry has browned.

title: chile cheese ball
directions: In food processor or large mixing bowl, thoroughly blend cream cheese and cheddar cheese.
Add chillies, onions and Worcestershire Sauce. Blend carefully so chilies are smashed. Divide mixture in 2 balls.
Roll each ball in chopped nuts and chill overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: In 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch Pyrex dish, dump prepared pie filling and spread out on bottom of dish.
Dump pineapple and juice on top of that, then carefully spread dry cake mix on top of that (directly out of the box).
Dot the margarine in thin slices on the top.
Sprinkle chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake in 350° preheated oven until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: middleman stew
directions: Brown ground beef. Remove from pan and saute green pepper and onion until soft. Drain grease from pan and add the cooked meat. Add all other ingredients and stir until blended. Cover pan and continue cooking over low heat for 45 - 60 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add salt to your taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake several potatoes one day.
The next day, grate potatoes. In loaf pan, put potatoes, soup (any kind of cream soup) and cheese; repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.
This can also be used with leftover mashed potatoes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put 1/2 of cheese in mixture.
Save other 1/2 for top.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugars and eggs well.
Add vanilla, then add flour, salt, soda, chips and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is hot, using top end of wooden spoon, punch holes in top of cake.
Mix cream of coconut and milk well.
Slowly pour over cake.
Cool completely.
To with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use 1/3 cup mix or less to mug of hot water.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: egg custard(over 60 years old)
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Add sugar and mix.
Add beaten eggs, milk and melted butter.
Pour in greased, shallow pan and bake in a hot oven about 20 minutes.

title: swedish cake
directions: Mix all by hand.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Stir in the next 9 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over tortillas.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 5 servings.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix together the instant pudding powder and 3 cups milk.
Fold in the thawed cool whip.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with squares of graham crackers (1 layer).
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of the graham crackers, then the rest of the pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers. Prepare the icing by mixing the cocoa, syrup, sugar and milk with the melted butter.
Beat until smooth.
Put on top of last layer of graham crackers and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Defrost bread dough.
Stretch and roll out bread.
Beat egg and add spices of your choice to beaten egg.
Brush egg mixture on each loaf of rolled bread.
Add layer of pepperoni (at least 1/4 pound on each), then add grated cheese and roll up.
Seal ends and edge. Bake according to directions on package (approximately 375° for 25 minutes); put a little butter on top of loaves before baking.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Mix all ingredients.
Mold into a loaf and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Pour tomato juice or tomatoes over loaf.
(Cholesterol conscious:
Substitute ground turkey for meat.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; add food color and Seven-Up gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook and continue to stir over medium heat until thick and clear; cool.
Pour over strawberries arranged in baked pie shell.
Serve with topping of choice.

title: baked beans #1
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large skillet, cook bacon 1 minute. Add beef and onions and cook, stirring with fork to break up meat. Brown meat.
Drain off grease.
Add catsup, sugar, brown sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Stir to blend.
Add the cans of beans and spoon all into a 3-quart casserole and bake 1 hour.

title: o-so-good pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add eggs.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° until set.

title: faye's sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Brown and crumble sausage and drain. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: white corn casserole
directions: Cook bacon and drain on paper towel.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Drain corn, adding salt and pepper.
Stir in onions, bacon grease and sour cream.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add corn and flour and mix well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: e z hot dish
directions: Chop pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Let stand overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Chicken soup may be served over the top.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cook the turkey breast.
Cool.
Cut into small cubes.
Add onions, sugar, pineapple and chutney.
Mix well.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Then add orange juice.
Add salt, pepper and Season-All.

title: turkey soup
directions: Break frame in half.
Place in a Dutch oven with water, 1 quartered onion and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Remove frame.
Cool.
Strain broth and return to Dutch oven or large pot.
Add turkey meat from frame. Add broth, pepper and tomatoes.
Stir in vegetables.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir in uncooked noodles; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve.
Great for leftover turkey!

title: three layer salad
directions: Dissolve both packages gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add cold water.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Work in enough additional flour to form dough that can be handled easily.
Roll very thin and cut with biscuit or cookie cutter. Bake at 375° until lightly browned, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: charlene's green beans (sweet & sour)
directions: Drain green beans and save liquid. Mix oil, vinegar, and sugar. Heat. Add beans and part of liquid. Serves 18.

title: chunky mustard potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a large saucepan. Add enough water to cover the potatoes and the 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Drain well. Cool for 10 minutes.

title: louisiana stew
directions: Combine flour, celery salt, black pepper and ginger and add garlic salt.
Sprinkle over stew beef and brown in bacon fat.
Add tomatoes, red wine vinegar, molasses, water and onion.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add carrots and cook until tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna surprise
directions: In medium size pan, place soup.
Add milk.
Drain tuna and add to soup.
Add drained peas to mixture.
Heat slowly, stirring to keep soup from sticking to pan.
When hot, pour over toasted bread wedges.
Serve with celery sticks filled with cream cheese.

title: pork chops 'n potatoes
directions: Lightly brown pork chops in skillet.
Place sliced potatoes in 2-quart greased baking dish.
Put pork chops on top.
Mix soup mix with water.
Pour water over pork chops and potatoes.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gon lo mein
directions: Place noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle noodles with 1/4 cup oyster sauce and 1 tablespoon sesame oil. Heat oven at 350°.
Place in oven for 6 to 10 minutes.
Slice mushrooms and other vegetables; stir-fry for 2 minutes in 1 tablespoon oil.
Season with salt, vetsin and the remaining 1/2 cup oyster sauce.
Mix the charsiu with vegetables.
Stir in noodles and toss gently.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Drop on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown the beef completely until cooked; drain.
Add onion, salt, pepper, catsup and tomato sauce.
Place biscuits on top of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Congeal Jell-O after mixing as directed on box. Add marshmallows and pineapple.
Keep stirring until congealed.
Mix instant vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Spread over mixture. Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread on top.
Let set overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and onion.
Add Worcestershire and form ball. Sprinkle with red pepper and roll in pecans.

title: chicken tetrazzini casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cattleman's spread
directions: In a skillet saute pecans and butter until golden brown.
In a mixing bowl beat cream cheese until smooth and add sour cream and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Stir in beef and onions.
Spread into a greased 8in. square dish and top with pecans.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 min.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick taco potatoes
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Add water and taco mix; stir.
Add salsa to meat mixture and simmer a few minutes.
Place cooked potatoes in baking dish.
Pour meat mixture into potatoes and stir together.
Top with fancy cheese and place in microwave or conventional oven long enough for cheese to melt. Serve hot.
Add a green salad and you have a quick meal!

title: rum cake
directions: Allow to boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove cake from oven, and pans.
Pour mixture over cake and let stand for 1 hour.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Keeps in refrigerator for 6 to 10 months.

title: baptist pie
directions: Combine all and whip thoroughly and pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 (10-inch) pies.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll into 1-inch balls.
Freeze hard on cookie sheet, then put in freezer bags until ready to bake.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, noodles, butter, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Heat through, but do not bring to a boil.
Serve immediately.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Butter a
2-quart
casserole
dish
or	spray with Pam. Cook macaroni, adding
2 drops of oil, until half cooked.
Put diced Velveeta in buttered casserole dish.
Drain macaroni and pour on top of cheese.
Stir up and cover with a lid.
Let set 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour in enough milk to cover the macaroni and stir up. Make sure
the
milk
is to the top of the macaroni. This will keep the macaroni from drying out.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Mix all other ingredients.
Marinate carrots overnight.
Serve cold.

title: sweet 'n sour beef stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, carrots, tomato sauce, salt, vinegar and 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; add to beef mixture.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles sprinkled with poppy seed, if desired.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Prepare Dream Whip with milk according to directions on package.
Fold prepared Dream Whip into peanut butter mixture.
Pour into shell.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Chill until firm.

title: beef cheese balls
directions: Chop up beef in blender and save 1/2 cup to roll the balls in. Mix together the cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, Accent and beef.
Divide this mixture to make 2 balls and roll in the 1/2 cup dried beef.
Let set 3 to 4 hours before using.
These freeze really well.

title: carrot salad
directions: One lemon and one orange or both boxes of orange jello should be prepared according to directions.
Size of box is optional. Once jello begins to set, add remaining ingredients in amounts desired according to personal preference.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine
mix, sugar and cinnamon.
Add the other ingredients. Beat
vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake
at
400° for 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and dip tops into melted butter and then into a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar
and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
(Also, ask your mother for help.)

title: paul's bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to a boil. Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook frozen broccoli per package directions and drain.
Place in 2-quart casserole and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion rice
directions: *Any other frozen whipped topping will do.

title: low-fat stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes and prick with
a fork.
Bake the potatoes in a 375° oven for 70 minutes or until done.
Slice the cooked potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out the inside, leaving the shells intact.
Mash the potatoes. Add sour cream, chives, milk, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon the potato mixture into each potato shell. Sprinkle tops with cheese and paprika.
Return to oven. Bake 10 minutes or until heated through.
If desired, place under broiler to lightly brown tops. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham jambalaya
directions: In heavy pan, brown ham lightly in butter.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, blend in tomatoes, Tabasco, water and rice.
Cover tightly; simmer 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Lift with fork occasionally (do not stir).
Serve garnished with parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook shrimp in boiling water 1 to 3 minutes or until done. Drain and set aside.
Cook celery and onion in oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook bacon slightly, add oleo and melt; add cooked squash, soup, onion, bell pepper, celery, eggs, 1/2 c crackers, and 1/2 c of grated cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and top with 1/2 c of cracker crumbs and 1/2 c cheese, paprika, few green onions.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat and melt together tomato soup and cream cheese and then cool.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup water, then add to cool soup mixture.
Put everything into a blender and stir or chop until everything is a creamy consistency.
Pour into a greased mold and chill several hours or overnight.

title: grandma's old fashion cream pie
directions: Mix in blender and pour in unbaked crust.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn down to 300° and finish baking for another 30 minutes or until set.

title: steak with sour cream
directions: Pound beef slightly.
Brown on both sides in butter and margarine.
Spread with sour cream; sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover and cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Boil eggplant, brushed with olive oil, until tender.
Pour in tomato sauce.
Sprinkle on cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and tossed salad.

title: billie sue's apricot dessert
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch and add to nectar in a saucepan. Cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool until just warm.
Break up 1 store-bought angel food cake into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. While mixture is still warm, pour over broken cake pieces.
Cool in refrigerator until set.
Cover with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: hamburger soup
directions: *The recipe
calls for peeling these vegetables, but in the interest of
adding
bulk to our diet, I simply scrub them well and use them peels and all.

title: spanish peanut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole(refrigerate overnight)
directions: Mix all ingredients well; cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in 13 x 9 pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out of oven 1/2 hour before serving.

title: hobo steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form patties.
Brown patties in skillet.
Line casserole dish and place patties in it.
Pour one can of cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) over all.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Pour sauces in crock-pot.
Add roast.
Cook 8 hours or until beef breaks apart and is stringy.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked dried lima beans(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cook dried lima beans until soft.
Combine all ingredients and top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: phyllis' spanish rice
directions: Crush tomatoes and return to juice.
Place all ingredients, except rice, in large pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Cook rice according to package directions.
When sauce and rice are cooked, mix them together in a large bowl.
Top with a little sour cream, if desired.

title: cornbread(zella ives' recipe)
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Sift cornmeal.
Put cornmeal back in sifter with flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir once again. Stir well.
Add buttermilk to eggs; stir well.
Add to dry mixture. Add more buttermilk to thickness you want.

title: carnival jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet. Cover skillet and bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Serves 4.

title: rich swedish cream dough
directions: Stir yeast into warm water to dissolve.
In a small bowl, mix well the dissolved yeast, cream, milk and egg yolks; set aside.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into small bite size pieces.
Pour all ingredients into a saucepan and add hot dogs.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Keep hot for serving as an appetizer or a party treat.

title: cherry shortcake
directions: Mix Bisquick, butter and milk.
Spread in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square cake pan (ungreased).
Spoon cherry pie filling over top of Bisquick mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or with ice cream on top.

title: ham dip
directions: Combine peppers, onion and ham.
Add cream cheese and Accent. Mix well and chill for 1 hour.

title: tex mex lasagna(non-messy taco meal; serves 8)
directions: Ready to bake in 20 minutes.
Great buffet party dish.

title: holiday hearth loaves
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, lemon peel and cinnamon.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in milk and lemon juice. Stir together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir until moist.
Fold in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon into greased loaf pan (5 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Very good.

title: world's most delicious cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Cream together butter and sugar, add egg and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time except pecans.
Mix until combined.
Stir in pecans.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake for 10 - 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not over cook.
Makes about 6 doz. cookies.

title: diabetic date-nut cake
directions: Cream butter and add eggs, Sucaryl and vanilla which have been beaten together.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other mixture. Beat with mixer on medium speed for several minutes until well blended.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix milk, flour, eggs and salt together.
*Use fat from roast and spread into 9 x 13-inch pan to cover bottom.
Heat in oven (425°) until very hot.
May even smoke.
Then add mixture and bake 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with gravy.
Especially good with standing rib roast.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Combine all ingredients. Chill.
Pour in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale last.

title: mexican slaw
directions: Chop and combine pepper, onion and tomatoes with cabbage.

title: tamales
directions: Cover meat with cold water; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until done, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
While meat is cooking, remove stems and seeds from chili pods (if you want it spicy, leave some seeds in); roast lightly in 1/4 cup oil, place in blender.
Add water, salt and cumin; blend until smooth.
Shred meat and brown in 1/2 cup oil; add chili mixture and cook for 7 minutes.
Soak corn husks for about 15 minutes; spread masa evenly over the larger husks.
Fill with about a tablespoon of however much it will hold.
Tear 1/2 inch strips of wet husks and use to tie up rolled tamales.
Steam for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: chinese chicken casserole(serves 12 to 14)
directions: Combine all but 1 can of noodles; put these on top with generous dots of butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with slice of bacon and place in slightly greased casserole in which dried beef has been arranged in 8 portions.
At this point, the dish can be frozen.
Mix sour cream and soup and spread evenly over chicken.
Do not salt.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: nut torte
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and beat 20 minutes, until fluffy. Add bread crumbs, nuts and vanilla.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; fold in other ingredients.
Grease pans very generously and line with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 minutes.

title: frosting for brownies
directions: Mix butter, milk and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil; boil 30 seconds.
Add chocolate chips.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: crinkly gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and molasses.
Beat together.
Sift the dry ingredients together; add creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Roll dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Fry hamburg and onion together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Boil 9 lasagna noodles in water and salt.
In 9 x 13-inch pan layer as follows:
Sauce, noodles, Mozzarella, sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, Parmesan, noodles, sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in a large bowl.
Set at high until smooth. Add half and half and beat at low until well mixed.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat until well blended for 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip, chocolate and pecans.
Spoon into crust.
Put in freezer until firm overnight.
Keep leftovers in freezer.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Precook and slice Italian sausage and add to beef broth.
Add cabbage, green pepper, onion, stewed tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked.
Add tortellini and simmer until soft.

title: potato finger thins
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into eighths.
Mix water and pepper sauce in shallow plate; dip strip into water, moisten on all sides.
Combine coating mix and cheese in plastic bag and shake strips to coat well.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet, sprayed with Pam and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.
Sprinkle with salt and serve immediately.

title: cheese potatoes in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cut in small pieces.
Dice egg fine. Chop onion.
Dice green olives.
Add Miracle Whip and mix well.
A little sugar may be added if desired.
Refrigerate.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken with celery stick, basil and butter.
Debone chicken when cooled and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 2 packages broccoli.
Mix together the cream of chicken soup, lemon juice, sour cream, mayo, Parmesan cheese and Velveeta; pour on top of chicken/broccoli mixture.
Cover with stuffing; dot with butter. Cover pan with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°; uncover and brown for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 2-quart dish; cover bottom then drain off excess.
Place all ingredients in dish.
Put crushed crackers on top and pour melted margarine over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream and butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Let the mixture boil for 10 minutes.
Then pour over the chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Beat until the chips and marshmallows have melted.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in a buttered baking dish.
Scald milk; add margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add salt, spices and vanilla.
Pour hot milk over eggs and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture over bread.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife put in center of pudding comes out clean.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with beaters until blended.
Add the oranges.
Bake 30 minutes or until done at 375°.
(Usually bake at the temperature recommended on the mix and for the recommended time.)

title: just real good cornbread
directions: Combine the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Turn into 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crust, and cook over medium heat until oleo melts.
Pour into crust and bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.

title: christmas chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in large heavy saucepan. Add milk and blend.
Then add sugar, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil.
Boil vigorously for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels and beat vigorously until morsels are melted. Then add marshmallow cream and continue beating until melted and well blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Turn into a well-buttered rectangular pan (12 x 7 x 2-inch).
Let sit at least 6 hours before cutting. Cut in large squares (the large ones stay much creamier and store in airtight container.
Yields approximately 4 pounds of fudge.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spread on top.
Lay other can of rolls on top to form a crust.
Beat egg white; brush over top layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: skillet yams and apples
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine over medium heat, add apples and onions and saute, stirring occasionally, until apples are soft, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar, lemon juice and seasonings.
Cook, stirring constantly until sugar is melted.
Add yam cubes and cook until yams are heated through.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until meat falls off bone.
In another pan boil your Rotini noodles.
Do not over cook the noodles the should be a little firm.
Dice and seed the tomatoes.
Once chicken has cooled separate meat from the bones.

title: apple-raisin dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
This is enough dressing for a 20 pound turkey.
If you wish to bake in casserole, just mix 1 cup of water, bouillon and a tablespoon of oleo; pour enough over dressing to moisten and bake at 350° until cooked through.
I usually cover with foil.

title: milton denfrod's hot sauce
directions: Chop up peppers and onions.
Mix all ingredients together in large cooker.
Bring to boil and heat thoroughly.
Place in jars and seal.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Mix butter, cocoa and Coke in a pan and bring to boil; watch it, stirring.
Add to flour and sugar and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well by hand.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Add sugar to oil.
Beat in eggs.
Mix cereal, flour and salt together.
Add baking soda to buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full with batter. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine.
Stir and add oatmeal and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Stir well.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: easy crust chicken casserole
directions: Skin chicken.
Cook chicken, remove bones.
Cut in small pieces and place in baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and chicken soup. Heat, stirring, until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix dry ingredients, put in margarine and add milk.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake at 350° until brown.

title: pernil (boston butt roast)
directions: Mix garlic, salt, Mojo and Sazon all together.
Make 1/2-inch holes into the pernil.
Fill the holes with this mixture.
Place in pan and cover with aluminum.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes, then turn over the meat, raise the temperature to 350° and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Meat will be done when the juice from meat is clear. After you turn meat you need to spoon juice over the meat.
Serve with white rice and gravy made from meat juice.

title: zippy sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat and add 2 packages little wieners or sausages.
The longer they simmer in the crock-pot, the better they taste.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In a small bowl, lightly beat egg whites and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine cocoa and cornstarch.
Whisk 3/4 cup of milk into cocoa mixture.
In large, heavy saucepan, combine remaining milk, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over high heat, whisking constantly.
Remove pan from heat.
Whisk cocoa mixture into hot milk mixture; bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Gradually whisk 1 cup of hot cocoa mixture into the egg whites. Pour mixture back into pan.
Cook over medium-low heat for 2 minutes, whisking constantly.
Do not boil.
Remove pan from heat. Add vanilla; blend well.
Pour pudding into serving dishes; cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Garnish with berries, mint leaves and cocoa.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll biscuits out, one at a time.
Cut wieners in half.
Roll biscuits around wieners; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook meat and sausage; drain.
In blender, mix whole tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, oregano and basil.
Add to meat mixture.
Bring to boil and lower heat to keep warm.
Boil lasagne noodles until done.
Drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer meat mixture, noodle, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Top layer should be meat mixture, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: world's best christmas cookies
directions: Cream
shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir
in
milk.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend into the other
mixture.
Divide
the
dough
in quarters.
Wrap in waxed paper
and
chill 1 hour.
Donate one of the quarters of the dough to children, for nibbling and sculpting.
(The dough may be colored with food coloring if you wish.) Roll the rest between floured
sheets of waxed paper to a thickness of about 1/8-inch. Cut
into
shapes
with cutters.
Bake in 375° oven for 6
to
8 minutes.
Cool
slightly.
Remove
to
rack.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes about 30 minutes until fork-tender.
Drain, cool, peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in 12-inch heavy skillet. Cook slowly over medium heat.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking until mixture reaches soft ball stage (236°) on candy thermometer.
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to just beyond soft crack stage (290° to 300°).
Add butter and soda, stirring to blend (will foam).
Pour into 2 large buttered baking sheets.
While warm, but still firm, turn it over and pull edges to stretch the brittle to make it thinner.
When cold break into pieces.
Makes about 2 1/4 pounds.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to full boil for 10 minutes. Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into greased dish. Let cool until set.

title: barbara's beef on a stick
directions: You will need small bamboo sticks.

title: brownies
directions: Beat together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs one at a time, then add the vanilla, chocolate, flour and baking powder. Stir in nuts if desired.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost brownies while still hot.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread the sugar cookie dough on a cookie sheet. Bake and let cool.

title: chocolate chew bake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Spread in greased 13-inch baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut while hot. Remove when cool.
Makes 18 large squares.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Fry on hot griddle. Makes 8 medium size pancakes.

title: italian chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in Italian salad dressing for 2 to 4 hours.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet or bake in oven until almost done.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Top with potatoes, carrots, and onions.
Pour water in bottom of dish.
Pour tomato sauce over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° until potatoes and carrots are done. Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Follow pie crust directions to prepare it for baking.
Boil chicken, cool, cut into chunks and set aside.
Melt butter; cook onion until limp.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and spices.
Add broth, stir and cook until thick.
Add cooked chicken and thawed vegetables.
Place mixture in pie pan; place uncooked dough on top.
Prick and bake according to dough directions.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook linguini; drain well.
Chop and add all vegetables.
Pour in bottle of dressing.
Add Salad Supreme.
Mix well.
Let marinate overnight.

title: grape wine(makes 2 gallons)
directions: 1st Week:
Mix together yeast, grapes and water.
Cover and place in a cool, dry place.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place onion and butter in a microwave-safe casserole dish. Cook 5 minutes.
Add corn meal mix, sour cream, eggs and corn (whole kernel corn must be drained).
Mix well and cook for 45 minutes at 300°.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook 10 more minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Dough will be cookie consistency. Spread dough into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
In a second bowl, mix the last 3 ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes (do not overbake).

title: warm shrimp salad
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok on high heat.
Saute shrimp until pink.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with crushed red pepper.
Add pea pods or peas.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add basil, vinegar and vodka.
Place on greens.
Top with onion slices.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Heat butter and oil in electric skillet.
Saute garlic and mushrooms until lightly golden.
Pound chicken pieces until thin. Coat chicken on both sides in flour that has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Remove garlic and mushroom pieces.
Add chicken pieces to skillet.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes on each side until lightly brown.
Remove from pan.
Add wine to pan.
Deglaze pan.
Add chicken broth.
Stir to make light gravy.
Add chicken pieces and mushrooms to gravy.
Heat several minutes until warm.
Serve as an accompaniment to potatoes, rice or pasta.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate several hours or overnight. For a little variety, you may add a cup of fresh grapes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Cut in Crisco with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn out on floured surface.
Knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: angel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese and whip. Add milk and whip.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Wash the greens thoroughly and place in a large or individual bowls.
Fry the bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Crumble into small pieces.
Top greens with sliced, hard-boiled eggs.
Pour Hot Bacon Dressing over the salad and top with chives and bacon.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Cool 1 minute; move to wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix vegetables in large bowl. Combine dressing ingredients and pour over vegetables. Mix thoroughly. Marinate for 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: moose pies
directions: Cream together the sugars, butter and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture by hand.
Add vanilla, nuts, oats and chocolate chips and mix well.
Drop by ice cream scoop onto ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes big cookies.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal together.
Add eggs, milk, lemon juice, lemon peel and melted butter or margarine.
Mix thoroughly and pour into unbaked deep 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until custard is done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 30 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil.
Mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tested done.
Contains 278 calories per serving.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box; cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still hot, punch holes in cake.
Pour milk over cake.
When cake is cool, mix Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake. Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan in oven at 350°.
Once melted, remove from oven and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl; add milk and lemon juice.
Stir to blend.

title: diabetic apple turnovers
directions: Roll each biscuit flat and 3 inches round.
Mix all remaining ingredients and put 1/4 cup apple mixture on each biscuit.
Fold over and pinch together.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350° or until biscuits are brown.
(These can be fried in oil.)

title: peanut clusters
directions: In the top of a double boiler, melt chocolate chips over hot, not boiling, water. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well; drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes about 35 clusters.

title: barbecue cheese sandwiches
directions: Chop fine the eggs, onion, pepper and olives.
Mix with cheese, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut buns in half. Spread each half with mixture.
Toast in a 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serves 3.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, onions and tomatoes (and garlic, if including) in oil.
Cook over low heat until tender, stirring occasionally. Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: paul's whipped cheese cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix in crock-pot (half of ingredients).
Slice orange and lemon to mixture; add sugar to taste.
Heat crock-pot on high and then turn down to low.
When needed, add the remaining mixture.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13 greased casserole at 450° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jerky marinade
directions: Slice meat thinly (1/4-inch slices).
Place in large glass or stainless container.
Add combined ingredients plus enough water to cover meat.
Soak meat in marinade overnight or at least 12 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: shrimp(butterfly, fried)
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tail.
Split down center of back; remove black vein.
Spread open and flat.
Rinse and dry.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in egg; gradually add water.
Beat until smooth.
Dip shrimp in batter.
Fry in hot fat at 375° for 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain.

title: print shop cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water (salted) just to cover bottom of pan until tender.
Set Cheez Whiz in boiling water to melt, stirring occasionally (or follow directions on jar to melt in microwave).
In large saucepan, heat margarine; stir in flour. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 quarts boiling water; stir until blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 quarts more boiling water with 2 chicken bouillon cubes dissolved in.
Return soup to heat; cook to rolling boil only until thick and smooth. Stir in melted cheese and undrained vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hearty homemade soup
directions: Brown meat on all sides in butter in Dutch oven. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for at least 2 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: herb-roasted chicken
directions: Stir all ingredients, except chicken, until well blended; set aside.
Wash chicken and wipe each piece dry.
Turn each piece in sauce (wet ingredients) to coat thoroughly.
Tuck thin edges of chicken under each piece, forming a compact shape, about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Place in shallow roasting pan and roast at 425° for 16 to 18 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add other ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: mexican shrimp cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, cornmeal, creamed corn, whole corn and milk together in a large bowl.
Chop onion and bell pepper in to the mixture.
Add salt, soda, 1/4 c. shortening, black and red pepper.
Mix well.
Add browned sausage and cooked shrimp to the mixture.
Mix well again.
Place remaining shortening into a 13 x 9 baking pan.
Grease all sides of pan well.
Pour mixture into the pan and bake for 1 hour.
Cool and slice into squares.
Serves 24.
May be used as an appetizer or as a sidedish

title: french toast
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Dip bread into batter.
Fry bread in bacon drippings. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: clam dip
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Mix crackers, clams, lemon juice, parsley and oregano.
Add onion and garlic mixture.
Place in ovenproof bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shiny chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soup, sour cream, sherry and mushrooms; pour over chicken breasts. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious served with rice.

title: graham cracker crisps
directions: Grease cookie sheet and place crackers on pan until full. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Combine butter and sugar in saucepan. Stir and heat until it just reaches the boiling point.
Pour butter and sugar mixture over the crackers until all are covered. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, dry yeast, sugar and salt together.
Add hot water.
In mixer on low mix oil and eggs together.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix, then add more flour.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to handle easy.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Put in 3 greased coffee cans which have been dusted with cornmeal. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato chutney
directions: Place all ingredients except mustard seed and oil in a saucepan and bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, until mixture is thick, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place frozen hash browns in a greased 3-quart baking dish. Top with melted margarine, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread over potatoes.
Place the grated cheese over the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: radiatori with avocado(or pasta with avocado)
directions: Bring large pot of water with a little olive oil to boil.
Add pasta.

title: old-fashioned date nut cake(recipe over 50 years old)
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter and eggs and set aside. Place flour in separate bowl.
Add dates and nuts, then put soda in cup of boiling water and pour over date-nut-flour mixture, then add alternately to first mixture.
Batter will be thin.)
Bake in a 7 x 11-inch pan at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cake stays moist. Serve with real whipped cream.

title: carrot and zucchini casserole
directions: Cook carrots and zucchini in small amount of boiling, salted water for 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain well, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Combine liquid with mayonnaise, onion, salt, pepper and horseradish.
Add to veggies, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased pan.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Make 2 layer cake according to package directions; freeze the layers for easy splitting into 4 layers.

title: banana bread (loaf recipe)(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and mix other ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
One-half cup of walnuts can be added, if desired.

title: deep dish cranberry apple pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; add combined egg and milk to flour mixture.
Stir in cheese.
Form into a ball.
Roll two-thirds of dough into a 15-inch square on a lightly floured surface.
Line an 8-inch square baking dish with dough.
Flute edges.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; toss with apples and cranberries.
Spoon into pastry shell; dot with margarine.
Roll out remaining dough to 12-inch square.
Cut into 1/8-inch strips. Place strips on fruit to form lattice; press to seal.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered toffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream just until it begins to thicken. Gradually add the ice cream topping and vanilla, beating until soft peaks form. Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers. Place the bottom layer on a serving plate; spread with 1 cup cream mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cup candy bar. Repeat. Place top layer on cake; frost top and sides with remaining cream candy bar. Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 12 to 14 servings.

title: macaroni with spinach and ham
directions: Chop the seasoned spinach,
press
into a buttered ring mold. Place in a pan of
hot
water to keep hot until serving time. Make white sauce
by melting butter, blending the flour into it, and adding milk
and seasoning.
Add ham chopped fine to the white sauce.
Remove
spinach
to platter surrounded by macaroni and fill center with creamed ham.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes. While still hot, poke holes in the top and pour on glaze.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: french salad
directions: Wash lettuce, tearing leaves into smaller pieces as you wash. Use a few sprinkles of vinegar to make sure lettuce is squeaky clean.
Set aside.
In a salad bowl, mix olive oil, canola oil and red wine vinegar.
Add plenty of salt.
Add garlic, red onion and tomatoes.
Let sit for 20 minutes.
Add lettuce.
Mix salad together to make sure lettuce is coated in dressing.
Add additional oil and vinegar as needed (4 parts oil to 1 part vinegar).
Serve with French bread.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, sugar and brown sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add oats, soda, peanut butter, corn syrup and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips and M&M's.
Scoop onto ungreased cookie sheet with cookie scoop.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.

title: quick crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers and chips.
Garnish with sliced green onions or fresh dill weed.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a deep sheet cake pan.
Cover the bottom of the cake pan with coconut and chopped pecans.
Mix the box of cake mix as directed on the box.
Pour cake batter into pan.
Cream 1 stick of butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Drop large spoonfuls across the top of batter with little spacing between drops.
Put into oven and bake for approximately 45 to 55 minutes.
The cream cheese mixture should sink into the cake and the cake will be cracked open, hence "Earthquake Cake".
The cake is done when the center springs back with a light touch.

title: squash casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in the order given.
Top with grated cheese. Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until brown and firm.

title: one hour homemade rolls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, mix the 3 cups flour, salt and yeast.
Put the honey and water into a quart jar and shake to mix well.
Add this mixture to the flour.
Stir and add one cup of flour at a time until you can no longer stir.
Then using your hands, knead very well.
Make rolls and place into a greased pan. Let rise about 15 to 20 minutes.
Place into the oven and bake for approximately 25 minutes (when golden brown, they are done).

title: pie crust - never fails
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Mix last three ingredients together.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Mix and proceed for any pastry.
Makes 2 double pie crusts.
Keeps well in refrigerator until needed.

title: pecan lassies
directions: Mix 1 stick butter, cream cheese and flour.
Make 24 one-inch balls and press into miniature muffin pans.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into pastry cups.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out and cool on towel.
May be frozen.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cook, covered, in an electric skillet (on medium heat) until tender.
Stir often.
Cook approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Bring syrup
and sugar to boil;
add the 3/4 cup peanut butter and
stir	until
dissolved.
Then stir in the cereal. Place in a
x 12-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips
and Crisco in the microwave or in a double boiler.
Pour over bars and cool.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, molasses and beaten egg.
Blend dry ingredients into first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill for 10 minutes. Take out, form into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil without stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Have popcorn in two shallow baking pans.
Pour mixture over corn and mix.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 2-quart baking dish. Drain 1/2 of juice from peaches.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour mixture into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour peaches in center; do not stir.
Bake about 45 minutes, until golden.

title: humdingers
directions: Cook dates, sugar, butter and milk until carmalized (about 5 minutes). Take off heat.
Add other ingredients.
Let cool.
Form into balls (about walnut size) and roll in 4X sugar.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: crab supper pie
directions: Sprinkle cheese over bottom of pie crust.
Top with drained crabmeat.
Sprinkle with onion flakes.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, lemon peel, mustard and nutmeg.
Pour over pie and top with almonds.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° or until pie is set.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Pile lightly into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese and chips.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sheep dip
directions: In food processor, mince onion and water chestnuts.
Add spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise and Swiss cheese.
On platter, cut center of bread out to leave a 2-inch crust around.
Place dip mixture in hole.
Cut center of bread into cubes and arrange around crust.
Serve and dip bread pieces in dip.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix and cook first four ingredients until thick.
Add shredded cheese; stir well.
Add pimentos and olives (olives are optional since they are very salty).
Add chilies and onions.
Mix well or put all in a blender and whip until smooth.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar gradually; blend well. Add 1 egg at a time; beat well after each egg.
Sift flour once. Add baking powder and salt; sift together 3 times.
Add flour; alternate with milk.
Add cocoa after eggs.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven for at least 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; add graham crackers (crushed).
Mix well; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese-bacon biscuits
directions: Mix flour, cheese, bacon and milk to form a sticky dough. Turn out on floured surface.
Knead 10 times.
Turn smooth side up and pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter dipped in flour.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: amish chicken corn soup
directions: Simmer chicken in boiling water until tender, remove bones and skin, strain the stock.
Return stock and chicken to the pot, add onions, celery and corn.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: spaghetti with tuna
directions: Drain the tuna and reserve the oil.
Place the reserved oil in a saucepan and heat.
Add the onion and garlic and cook over low heat until lightly browned.
Add the tuna and tomato sauce.
Cook over low heat for about 15 minutes
or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Add the parsley.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mash together well.
Keep warm in small crock-pot.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in a very small amount of water.
Do not drain.
Lower heat to simmer.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and 1 cup milk.
Add to hot vegetables and stir well.
Add 2 cups milk and simmer until thickened and hot.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Will serve 6.

title: cream of carrot-cheddar soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add and simmer vegetables, broth and seasonings.
Stir occasionally.
Add milk and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.
Discard bay leaf.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet; drain. Layer ground chuck, potatoes, onions and cheese in 9 x 9 baking dish. Mix soup and water. Pour mixture over layers. Cover and bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake about 20 minutes longer.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Make jello with hot water.
Add pineapple and raspberries (juice and all).
Place 1/2 mixture in 8-inch square dish. Refrigerate until almost set, 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon sour cream over mixture.
Then spoon rest of jello mixture over sour cream. Chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook
all
the	ingredients in a saucepan over a medium flame until thick.
Pour into a precooked pie shell.
Top with a meringue and brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze beef; thinly slice across grain into bite size strips.

title: carrot and green bean casserole
directions: Cook onion slightly in oil.
Add flour and seasoning.
Blend well; add milk gradually and cook until slightly thickened.
Add eggs and cook slowly 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add grated cheese and stir in vegetables.
Pour into greased baking dish; cover with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: grilled barbecue steak
directions: Cut garlic in half.
Rub over both sides of steak.
Spread mustard over steak and place in shallow glass dish.
Cover with soy sauce, grated onion and minced garlic halves.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours, turning several times.
Prepare coals to high heat.
Remove steak from marinade and place steak on oiled grid or hinged double rack 4 inches from hot coals; sear for 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn steak and raise grid to 5 inches from hot coals.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes for rare, 10 minutes for medium or 15 minutes for well done.

title: chicken broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, followed by layers of chicken and then broccoli.
Spread the soup over these ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° or until cheese is bubbly.

title: grandma's mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together then add the rest.
Blend well. Pour batter into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpicks comes out clean.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar (being sure that it is a good full cup), then add flour.
Add a little at a time, melted oleo and milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and onion.
Mix in chicken, nuts and celery. Top with cheese and cover with potato chips. Bake in an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex pan at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: marinated baked chicken
directions: In measuring cup, combine salad dressing and soy sauce.
Pour 3/4 cup of dressing in a large Ziploc plastic bag.	Add chicken. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight, turning several times. Refrigerate remaining marinade for basting.
Drain chicken, discarding marinade.
Place chicken, skin side up, on a rack in a roasting pan.
Sprinkle with onion salt and garlic salt.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until juices run clear or 170° on meat thermometer.
Brush occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: pepperoni hors d'oeuvre
directions: Roll out dough long and thin over floured board.
Using pastry brush, brush egg on dough, then sprinkle grated cheese over all. Put pepperoni over entire surface.
Roll up lengthwise, jelly roll style.
Brush with egg for browning.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Slice in dics.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Mix in the chicken and the mushroom soup. Add water and stuffing mix; combine well. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil in sugar; mix in the eggs until frothy.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix in carrots and nuts.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on rack.
Use cream cheese icing or vanilla icing.

title: substitute scrapple
directions: Cook hamburger,
seasonings
and water until it boils.
Add corn meal as much as
is necessary and flour to help set up.
Pour into pans and cool.
Slice and
fry.
This
is a good substitute! We like it hot from the kettle and never have leftover to fry.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Season chicken breast with salt and pepper to taste.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in flour.
Fry in skillet until brown on each side.
Drain off grease and add soup diluted with water to make gravy.
Cover and simmer until tender, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit and mix gently.
Combine remaining ingredients and
sprinkle
over
fruit.
Bake in uncovered casserole dish at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: swedish christmas cookies(meringues)
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff and dry.
Fold in sugar gradually and lastly add the vanilla.
Fold in ground nuts.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheets or cookie sheets covered with parchment paper at 300° or 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until just beginning to brown.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Beat egg, vanilla and melted butter in bowl.
Add flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Ingredients will be slightly dry and crumbly.
Add nuts.
Dissolve baking soda in pineapple (do not drain) and add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients slowly.
Do not boil.
Pour over cereal in big bowl and mix.
Put 1/4 powdered sugar in paper bag, then cereal, then sugar, etc., ending with sugar.
Shake bag to coat cereal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
In another mixing bowl, combine sugar, shredded zucchini, cooking oil, egg and lemon peel.
Mix well. Add flour mixture; stir just until combined.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: hot and hearty potato salad
directions: Saute onion in butter. Stir in mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Add and heat the potatoes but don't boil. Garnish with parsley and bacon.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 1 tablespoon melted butter or margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and chives; mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 squares. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture in each square.
Pull 4 corners to top and twist to seal.
Brush with remaining butter; dip in bread crumbs.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chicken spread
directions: Blend and refrigerate.
Good with Chicken in a Biskit crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Stir in water.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: fusilli with sausage marinara and mozzarella
directions: Crumble the sausage into a large skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until browned, about 10 minutes.
Add the onion and cook for 5 minutes more.
Stir in marinara sauce; bring to a boil.
Toss the sauce with the hot pasta and Mozzarella in a serving bowl.
Makes 6
servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Measure into bowl and stir. Butter pan. Pour into pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all together well, using spoon, in large bowl.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: turtle cake dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package. Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Unwrap caramels and melt with evaporated milk and butter/margarine in saucepan over low heat. Pour caramel mixture over hot cake spreading evenly. Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped pecans on caramel mixture. Top with remaining cake batter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: angel food delight
directions: Mix pineapple with angel food cake mix. Pour into flat pan and bake 30 minutes at 250°. Use a 9 x 11 or 13 pan. You can put Cool Whip on it after it cools and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf with mashed potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1/2 cup of the soup, beef, onion, crumbs and egg.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, firmly shape into an 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove meat loaf from oven; pour off fat.
Turn oven to 450°.
Prepare mashed potatoes.
Spread over meat loaf.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes until potatoes just begin to brown.

title: philly christmas cake
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs.
Gradually add flour and baking powder.
Combine 1/4 cup flour with fruit and 1/2 cup nuts.
Fold into batter.
Grease 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Garnish with candied pineapple slices and cherries.

title: eggplant a la riegeldale
directions: Peel and slice eggplant; cook until mushy done.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and a little of the butter.
Mix well and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese, crumbs and butter mixture. Bake in moderate oven, about 25 or 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in oats.
Combine other ingredients in separate bowl and add to flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes 2 dozen (3-inch diameter) cookies.

title: vanilla wafer dessert
directions: In saucepan combine pineapple juice, orange juice and salt; bring to boil.
Add marshmallows.
Stir constantly until melted. Refrigerate mixture until slightly thickened, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
In bottom of ice cube tray place layer of cookies.
Top marshmallow mixture with cookies. Refrigerate 8 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix pineapple and pudding mix in bowl.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip to desired consistency (add juice if too dry).

title: mom's everyday cookie dough
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Dissolve soda in milk. Add and blend.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour and salt, then stir in flour gradually.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll 1/4 to 1/8-inch thick; cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased sheet 8 minutes at 350°. Decorate when cool.

title: skillet barbecue pork chops
directions: Spray 12-inch nonstick skillet with cooking spray; heat over medium heat. Sprinkle both sides of pork with salt and pepper. Cook pork about 5 minutes, turning once until brown. Mix remaining ingredients. Add to skillet. Heat to boiling and reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally until pork is tender.

title: johnnie's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, chocolate mixture, buttermilk and soda.
Add flour last.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: popcorn honey balls
directions: Melt butter, sugar and honey in pot. Heat on high until mix bubbles around edges of pot.
Pour over popcorn.
Make into ball shapes. Let cool on wax paper.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo, stir in sugar and syrup. Bring to a boil and boil one minute without stirring.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well; chill.
Store in airtight container. Keeps very well in refrigerator for weeks.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except cornbread mix.
Make cornbread according to directions.
Pour on top of beef and beans. Bake at 350° until cornbread is done.

title: how to make apple butter
directions: In 15 gallon kettle add water and apples.
Cook several hours or until it doesn't weep.
Add sugar, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Continue cooking for at least 1 hour longer.
Yields about 12 gallons.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla flavoring; mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip by hand. Divide into 2 crusts.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or all day. Top with blueberry pie filling.
Serves 16.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Brown onion lightly in butter; add paprika and pepper.
Add cut up chicken.
Stir slowly until well done.
