Take the sour cream, mix in 1 tablespoon flour and stir into chicken.
Do not boil but simmer until it thickens slightly.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Flatten chicken until 1/4 inch thick with meat tenderizer.

title: baked pineapple pudding
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Beat eggs with fork add pineapple and mix together.
Add the sugar, flour and salt to this and stir together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and pour melted margarine over bread.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut eggplant thin, dip in beaten egg then dip in flour.
In a frying pan with heated oil, fry eggplant slices till golden brown. Turn and cook on other side.
Remove and drain on paper towel. Season with salt and pepper.
Place spaghetti sauce on bottom of baking dish and add eggplant slices, layering with sauce.
Can add pepperoni, if desired.
Bake 350° for 45 mins. -1 hour. Add parmesan cheese when done.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch); line with buttered bread. Top with cheese, ham and buttered bread.
Mix eggs (beaten), milk, mustard and salt and pour over sandwiches.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Just before baking, top with corn flake crumbs and pour melted butter over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandmother's jelly roll
directions: Mix, bake in shallow cookie sheet, spread with jelly or jam; roll up in a towel or wax paper.
Slice when warm or cool.
No oven temp given in this 1948 recipe.
Suggest 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yummy!

title: taffy apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Insert wood skewers in apples.
Place sugar, corn syrup, water and vinegar in saucepan and stir.
Place in oven on low heat and cook to hard ball stage (300°) or until syrup separates into threads.
Dip in candy mixture and place on wax paper to cool.

title: wet and wild berry slush
directions: In a blender, combine strawberries, frozen juice and sugar. While blending, add ice cubes through hole in lid until slushy. Grab a straw and start sipping.
Serves 4.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: In glass bowl, combine pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Fold in dry pudding mix, blending well.
Serve at room temperature or chill and garnish with chopped pecans and maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and sugar in hot water until dissolved; add pineapple juice.
Stir constantly.
Add water to make 1 gallon. Freeze overnight.
Take out of freezer and clip with pick or knife.
Add ginger ale.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan over medium heat; stir well. Simmer over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Brush on chicken, pork chops and hamburgers.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil in large pan over medium heat. Boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and chips.
Beat with electric hand mixer on high until all is blended.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in squares and keep in covered container in refrigerator.

title: super meat loaf
directions: Place bread in blender until finely ground.
Add to meat. Combine water, celery and onion in blender until blended.
Add egg and blend.
Add to meat mixture and place in loaf pan and score top.
Top with mixture of 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 2 tablespoons catsup.
Cook 18 to 20 minutes in microwave.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Can be baked in regular oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Mix Jell-O with the Miracle Whip, celery, onion, green pepper and corned beef.
Put into refrigerator until firm.
Slice hard-boiled eggs on top (optional).
Mix lime Jell-O as directed and pour on top. Let set.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook slowly for about 40 minutes. Also use all your chicken stock in stew.
This is very good.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir to soften lemonade concentrate.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Garnish with graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cookies
directions: Mix eggs, shortening, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add enough flour to thicken to dough.
Roll or spoon out on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° until golden.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Fry bacon in deep skillet. Remove slices. Drain and reserve the grease. Add the onions, potatoes, salt and boiling water to the bacon grease. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes. During the last 5 minutes, add the broccoli that has been pureed with water (just enough to puree) in a blender. Melt butter in a separate saucepan. Blend in flour and bouillon. Add milk and cook until thickened. Add to broccoli mixture and heat. Add pepper and Accent. Crumble bacon fine. Can be added to the soup or added as a garnish. Use about 6 medium potatoes for the shredded potatoes. Also fresh broccoli can be used, 1 1/2 cups. Serves 8.

title: onion pretzels(a.k.a. penn state pretzels)
directions: Mix melted butter/margarine and soup mix in small bowl.
Place broken pretzels into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour melted mixture over pretzels and stir.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: louisiana alligator sauce
directions: Carefully remove all fat from alligator meat.
Cut into bite size pieces and set aside.
Saute pepper, onion, celery and garlic in oil until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients except the meat and simmer in a covered pot for 30 minutes.
Add alligator meat and continue cooking for 1 1/2 hours.
Add salt and red pepper to taste.
Allow to cool to room temperature, then reheat and serve over rice.

title: dessert or savory fritters
directions: Melt package of semi-sweet chocolate in small saucepan.
Dip in large clean strawberries.
Place on wax paper and serve.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Cover in cold water and soak overnight.
Cook sausage, onions and garlic until slightly browned.
Add beans, ham bone and water to cover 1 inch over beans.
Add pepper, salt and sugar to taste.
Cook slowly for several hours.
Serve over rice.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Blend well.
Add flavorings.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: marinated cube steaks
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Marinate cube steaks in the refrigerator at least 3 hours, best overnight.
Grill or broil 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream
butter,	Crisco,
sour
cream
and
sugar
until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time,
mixing after each addition. Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add flavor.
Mix well.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour and mix well.
Dough will be very soft.
May be stored in refrigerator to be used as needed.
Grease muffin pans.
Fill half full (do not let rise) and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: tropical fruit cloud salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from tropical fruit.
Combine reserved juice, water and orange gelatin.
Heat until dissolved. Fold in whipped topping.
Mix in tropical fruit, cottage cheese and nuts.
Chill.

title: turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Do not overcook.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the broccoli and turkey.
Prepare sauce by mixing remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over broccoli and turkey.
Top with crumbs and butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
You may also use chicken or ham instead of turkey.
Yields 10 servings.
Preparation time is 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beckham place creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except last two and bring to a boil. Simmer five minutes.
Blend butter with flour, add to the corn mixture, mix well and remove from heat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin squares(light recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place all the ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Blend well. Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread batter evenly.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 squares.
Contains 107 calories per square.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat 1 minute.
Mix cocoa and coloring in a cup to make a paste. Add to creamed mixture.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add flour (sift 3 times) and milk alternately.
Sprinkle soda over batter; then pour vinegar over batter and stir until well blended.
Do not beat after adding soda and vinegar.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt Parkay (butter) in frypan.
Add onions, celery and garlic. Cook slowly until tender but not brown.
Add flour and seasonings; stir until blended.
Stir in green pepper and tomatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: flavored rice
directions: In 3-quart pan, bring to boil water and margarine.
Stir in rice, salt, bouillon and parsley.
Cover.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Spicy Polish sausages or Bratwurst are wrapped in a simple-to-prepare flaky pastry that is made with cottage cheese. After baking, you slice each bundle into 1-inch pieces.
Serve speared with a cocktail pick.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Stirring often, saut the celery, green pepper and onion in the oil over medium heat until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Stir in the oregano and then the flour or cornstarch if you want a thicker sauce.
Add the tomatoes with their juice. Add the soup, stirring to mix well, and cook until hot.
Let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the shrimp, stirring to mix well.
Cover the pot; turn off the heat and let the flavor ripen for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix rice with a cup of water.
Spread in a roasting pan. Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours and don't peek.

title: bishop's bread(biskopen's brod)
directions: Mix sugar and eggs well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add whole nuts, cherries, dates and chocolate.
Hand mix. Prepare loaf pan by lining with heavy waxed paper.
Pour batter into lined pan.
Cover loosely with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Fold back waxed paper when batter has risen (about 50 to 60 minutes after it has been in the oven).

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, water chestnuts and celery in butter.
Add other ingredients and heat over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.

title: rhubarb jello salad
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1 inch pieces.
Cook the rhubarb with sugar and water until soft.
Add water, if necessary, so that you will have 3 cups cooked rhubarb.
While rhubarb is very hot, stir in dry Jell-O and mix until Jell-O is dissolved.
Chill until firm.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix
the
first
ingredients
together
and place in cabbage leaves.
Cover with a mixture of the soup, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cover with foil.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done.
Drain thoroughly.
Cook the grated carrots in 1 cup of water.
Be certain they
are thoroughly cooked.
Drain and dry out the excess liquid on paper towels.
Beat egg; add most of the sour cream, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes and beat with electric beater.
Add the can of milk to potatoes a little at a time and taste.
Add more salt, pepper and dry mustard, if desired (careful with the dry mustard); add more sour cream.
Potatoes must be thin like cake batter.
They will dry out when baked.
Fold in grated carrots and half of the cheese.
Place in Pyrex dish (9 x 14-inch).
Sprinkle balance of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is golden brown.
This dish may be prepared days in advance and baked before serving.

title: oatmeal, raisins and pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars until smooth; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine and blend thoroughly flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: crab dip
directions: In a bowl, blend all ingredients.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown chops.
Season with seasoned salt.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup of the cheese and 1/2 can of the onion rings. Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chops over potato mixture.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 to 7 minutes more.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Beat together eggs, oil and pumpkin. Add dry ingredients. Add chocolate chips. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Add mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and
15 minutes.

title: chicken breast and shrimp
directions: Dip chicken breasts in egg and water mixture.
Season with salt, pepper and red pepper to taste.
Roll chicken in Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Saute shrimp and onions.
Spread this on chicken breasts.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Lay rolled chicken in a pan in which margarine has been melted.
Add sherry. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting with pan juices.

title: crabmeat dip(club member: nicholas thompson)
directions: Spread cream cheese in dish. Layer crabmeat on top of cheese. Mix the 3 sauces. Spread over crabmeat. Great with chips.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss cooked, drained penne in 2 tablespoons olive oil. Combine remaining olive oil, tomatoes, cheese, beans, vinegar, basil, parsley and season.
Add to pasta and toss.
Add a little extra oil and vinegar, if necessary.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 or larger square pan, mix pie filling, pineapple and 1 cup sugar or less to taste. Sprinkle entire cake mix (dry) onto the top of the mixture. Pat down until dry mix soaks up some of the juice. Melt the butter and spoon entire stick onto dry mix. Sprinkle sugar on top of butter. Next, sprinkle pecans on top of sugar. Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes. Check. Bake until desired brown color and texture.

title: pear cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition; set aside.
Sift flour with cinnamon, salt and soda, then add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts, coconut, dates and pears.
Stir by hand.
Batter will be thick. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.
Cool on rack until cake shrinks from sides of pan.
Remove from pan to complete cooling.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling point. Serve.

title: cherry pie squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and almond extract together, then add flour, mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling on batter and top with remaining batter and spread it out (it won't quiet cover all). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mapely crunch popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine popcorn and peanuts; set aside. Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in syrup and cinnamon. Bring to rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn, tossing to coat evenly.

title: cream cheese brownie
directions: Prepare pie crust as on package. In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg; beat until smooth. Set aside.

title: company baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and chopped onion until bacon is crisp; drain. Drain beans; mix with remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a 2 1/2 quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine and mix together.
Add 1/2 cup nuts or 1/4 cup raisins, if desired.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325° in 2 small tins or 1 large bread pan.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: fry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in liquid.
Dough may be sticky.
More flour can be worked in as dough is kneaded for about 3 minutes.
Allow to stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Cover with cloth or plastic wrap.
Divide dough into 15 pieces.
Flour your hands.
Make each piece into a 3-inch round.
Cover again for 10 minutes.
Fry in 2-inches of oil to 340° to 350° in frypan or skillet, about 1 minute on each side.
Drain on paper towel. Serve with cinnamon and sugar or any jam.

title: crispy golden chicken
directions: Mix together egg and water.
Mix the following:
flour, salt, baking powder, paprika and pepper.
Dip the chicken in the egg mixture and then into the flour.
Place chicken on cookie sheet in which 1/4 pound butter has been melted.
Do not place chicken pieces on top of each other.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven. Bake on one side 45 minutes and then turn and bake on the other side 45 minutes.

title: german pizza
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, brown beef with onion, green pepper and half of salt and pepper.
Remove meat mixture from skillet; drain fat.
Reduce heat to low and melt margarine in skillet, spread potatoes over margarine and sprinkle with remaining salt.
Top with beef mixture, combine eggs and milk and pour over all.
Cook, covered, about 30 minutes.
Top with cheese, cover, and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add vinegar, mixing well.
Stir in raisins, pecans and coconut.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 Tbsp. butter until soft. Add next 5 ingredients. Separate dough into four rectangles and seal perforations. Spoon 1/2 c. cheese mixture into each square. Pull corners to top, twist slightly and seal edges. Place on cookie sheet. Brush tops with reserved 1 Tbsp. butter and sprinkle with croutons. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Serve with a basic white sauce.

title: festive fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken strips in picante sauce, oil and lemon juice for several hours. Chop onion and pepper and add to the chicken marinating
and either cook on the grill on top of foil or stir-fry in pan on stove.
Can be served with chopped tomato, shredded cheese, guacamole and sour cream.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Mix everything together and put into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Top with Fluffy Icing.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt; drain thoroughly.
Blend soup, cheese and egg.
Add mayo and milk; stir in broccoli.

title: hot cheesy biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and red pepper.
Cut in butter and add grated cheese.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk until dough is well moistened.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Crumble 1 1/2 pounds cooked and drained sausage.
Grease 9 x 15-inch pan or casserole.
Cover bottom of pan with 1 box seasoned croutons.
Top croutons with 2 large packages of grated cheese. Add cooked and drained sausage.
Mix together and beat well eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over croutons, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Pour mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 cup milk, over mixture and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until brown.

title: piggybank pork bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Stir in noodles, soup, corn (with liquid) and cheese.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients and shortening.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture.
Mix well, but don't overhandle the dough as that makes it tough.
Divide into 5 balls.
Roll each ball on lightly floured surface into circle for crust.
Makes 5 crusts.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into 2 pie crusts. Garnish with mini chocolate chips, if desired.
Freeze at least 6 hours.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.
Return unused portion to freezer.

title: mock grape leaf pickles
directions: Boil solution for 7 minutes.
Pour over beets and seal at once in preheated jars.
Leave in canner 10 minutes in order to seal.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and chill for several hours.
Form into buckeye size balls and dip halfway into chocolate and paraffin that has been melted together in double boiler over boiling water.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook broccoli as directed and drain. Arrange spears in a 9 x 9 casserole pan. Spread cream of mushroom soup over broccoli. Sprinkle garlic salt over top. Cut squares of Velveeta cheese and place on top. Melt margarine and soak bread crumbs into margarine. Sprinkle on top. Bake in the oven about 20 minutes.

title: barbecued vegetable kabobs
directions: Thread vegetables on 6-inch long skewers, placing 2 pieces of each vegetable on each 6-inch skewer.
Brush with barbecue sauce and sprinkle with crushed basil.
Place on broiler tray in range. Cook slowly until vegetables are crisply cooked, about 20 minutes. Onions will be crisp, softer onions will require parboiling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rhubarb crumb
directions: Mix until crumbly sifted flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Put half of the crumbs in a 9-inch pan with rhubarb.

title: vegetarian rice casserole
directions: Chop the following vegetables in large chunks:
onion, green peppers, celery and tomatoes.
In vegetable oil or olive oil, lightly brown onions and add green peppers and celery.
Simmer and add tomatoes.
Sprinkle a bit of red cayenne pepper and basil over simmering mixture.
Cover and cook down until tender.
Add tomato sauce.
If mixture requires more liquid, add water.
Stir in long grain brown rice and simmer 45 to 55 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
Broil until bubbly and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer half broccoli, half cheese, half butter and half of crackers.
Repeat for another layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine seasonings with the softened cheese.
Roll into cheese ball.
Roll ball
in
nuts	and parsley flakes.
Chill. Serve at room temperature
with assorted crackers.
(May use a small can of deviled ham in cheese ball.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Boil pasta and drain.
Mix pasta, sauce and some of the cheeses.
Add the pepperoni and any other toppings.
Top with remaining cheese and bake in 350 degree oven till bubbly.
Serve with salad and bread and enjoy.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In skillet in butter, saute onions and celery until cooked. Add soup, pimentos and jalapeno pepper.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth (salted).
Mix chicken, skillet mix and spaghetti.
Add black pepper to taste and paprika for color.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain and mix in taco seasoning mix.
Let simmer.
Mix cornmeal mix, eggs, milk, corn, green chilies and black olives.
Pour half of the batter into an iron skillet.
Add meat and sprinkle on cheese.	Pour the remaining batter over the meat and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hr. and 20 minutes.

title: ribbon sandwiches
directions: Combine the ingredients together.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix butter, sugar and eggs. Blend flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Slowly mix dry ingredients with wet. Knead dough. Split into 2 portions. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 1 hour. Roll into small balls. Roll in sugar and cinnamon. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grandma's creamed rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on box using canned milk; add butter and sugar.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Eggs should be added one at a time, beating slowly.
Add to mixture the vanilla and 2 cups cake flour (sifted).
In a separate bowl mix pecans, diced cherries and pineapple with 2 cups of regular flour.
When well mixed, pour into other mixture.
Add coconut and stir until well mixed.
Pour into two loaf pans and cook at 250° for 2 hours with pan of water underneath.
Take water out and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: apple french toast
directions: Spray a rectangular casserole dish with cooking spray. Cut French toast into 1 inch cubes and place in dish. Microwave milk on high 1-1/2 to 2 minutes. Whisk eggs and add milk slowly as you whisk. Pour into dish with toast and mix gently, set aside.

title: jack's chili
directions: Brown beef. Pour off excess liquid. Add onion. Cook beef well and onions softened. Add tomato paste, chili beans, diced tomatoes and water to desired consistency. Add pepper, salt, chili powder and sugar. Simmer on low for at least 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter, shortening and sugar on high speed until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes). Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Beat in vanilla and lemon juice.
Gradually add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Use a scant 1/4 cup of dough for each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: best-ever homemade pizza
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Simmer over low heat 1 hour or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.
Spread sauce evenly over each pizza crust, leaving a 1/2-inch border around edges.
Bake until edges are brown.

title: sloppy jane's
directions: Brown the meat.
Add relish and soup.
Do not dilute the soup. Simmer for 20 minutes.
If too thick, add chili sauce.
Makes about 6 sandwiches.

title: p. b. balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Roll into balls and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate almond bark in microwave; melt at 15 second intervals to prevent burning.
Use a toothpick to dip balls into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: strawberry and spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach leaves.
Wrap in damp paper towels; chill in refrigerator.
Hull and slice strawberries; place in bowl. Sweeten with 1 tablespoon sugar; chill.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and pepper.
Layer alternately with tortillas which have been dipped in broth to soften in a shallow 3-quart greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt.
Combine soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes and spoon over this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 5 hours.
May be served with crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: In a crock-pot (no heat), soak beans in water overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 11 to 12 hours or high heat for 4 to 5 hours.

title: fat-free chocolate sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir and cook constantly until thick and bubbly. Cook for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter until smooth; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven, then add chocolate chips on top while still hot and spread when soft.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over frozen vegetables.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish.
(Can refrigerate a day or so.
Good to set out 2 hours before heating.)
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Layer in large casserole dish 1/2 potatoes, 1/2 hamburger meat, and 1/2 Velveeta.
Repeat layers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut cabbage and green pepper.
Add beans, tomatoes and water over the top to make soup.
Cook until cabbage is done.
While this is cooking, brown beef and drain off grease and add to cabbage.
Add chili powder.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Coarsely chop graham crackers with food chopper; combine with oleo and sugar.
Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine topping, pudding and sour cream in bowl with a whisk.
Pour half of filling over the crust.
Slice bananas and layer on top.
Pour remaining filling over bananas.
Finely chop pecans and sprinkle over top.
Sets immediately, but can be refrigerated to chill.

title: vegetable congealed salad
directions: Dissolve cream cheese in warmed tomato soup; set aside.
Heat 1/4 cup water until warm and dissolve gelatin.
Combine gelatin with cream cheese and soup; cool.
Add vegetables to cooled mixture.
Pour into large square cake pan.
Chill until firm. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add oil, vanilla and salt.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: roast chicken(crock-pot)
directions: Thoroughly wash chicken and pat dry.
Sprinkle cavity generously with salt, pepper and parsley.
Place in Crock-Pot and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with parsley and basil or tarragon, if desired.
Cover and cook on High 1 hour, then Low 8-10 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut tenderized round steak in bit size pieces.
Bake until done.
On top of stove mix:
gravy mixes, water, pepper, tomatoes, and soy sauce.
Add meat.
Cook rice.
Serve over rice.

title: green jello salad
directions: Blend all together and refrigerate.

title: vegetable beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet; drain off excess grease.
Add tomato sauce and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from flame; add mixed vegetables and 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese to beef mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spoon mixture into greased baking dish.
Separate the biscuits into two for a total of 20.
Line the outer edges of the mixture with the biscuits, forming a rectangular opening in the center.
Layer the remaining cheese in the opening.
Brush the melted butter on the biscuit tops and bake for 22 to 27 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Remove large veins from spinach and tear into small pieces. Combine spinach, eggs and bacon.
Add onions; toss lightly.
Just before serving, add dressing and salt.

title: s'mores indoors
directions: Heat syrup, butter and chips to boiling in large saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large mixing bowl.
Toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows 1 cup at a time. Press mixture evenly in pan with piece of waxed paper.
Let stand until firm at least 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: shredded pork(mochonos)
directions: In saucepan, bring meat, water, onion and salt to boiling; simmer, covered, for 1 hour until meat is tender.
Uncover; boil rapidly 15 to 20 minutes or until most of water evaporates.
Watch closely and stir so meat doesn't stick.
Using 2 forks, finely shred meat.
In lightly greased skillet, fry meat until it resembles golden threads.
Put on platter and garnish with lettuce, tomato slices and guacamole.
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: sausage, pepper, potato bake
directions: Place sausage in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Drain fat.
Add potatoes, peppers and onions.
Pour dressing over top. Add water and seasonings.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake at 400° to brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar until soft.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add in two additions.
Beat well after each addition; fold in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: charlie brown cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well. Grease but do NOT flour 8 x 12 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Pour Eagle Brand condensed milk over cake. Sprinkle with coconut. Sprinkle on nuts. Bake 15 minutes more. Ice with chocolate frosting or semi-sweet chocolate chips.

title: roasted chicken
directions: In bowl, combine seasonings.
Rub in chicken, inside and out, patting mixture to evenly distribute deep in skin.
Place in sealable plastic bag, seal and refrigerate, covered, overnight. Place onion in bird cavity.
Roast, uncovered, at 250° for about 5 hours, basting occasionally, with pan juices or until pan juices start to caramelize on bottom of pan and chicken is golden brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: orange punch
directions: Fill 3 ice cube trays with a mixture of Kool-Aid, sugar and water; freeze.
Combine all remaining ingredients and mix well. Before serving, pour into punch bowl and add orange ice cubes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, Karo syrup and water together until they form a hard mass in cold water.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually blend with syrup mixture, beating constantly.
When mixture begins to stiffen, add nuts and drop from teaspoon onto greased plate.
Candied cherries make a pleasing addition.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Beat together margarine, egg and sugar.
In another bowl, mix together flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Mix the two sets alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Fill greased muffin tins 1/3 full. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Roll in a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon while still warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Bring 1 cup of rice to a boil and cover for 5 minutes.
Melt butter and put in onion, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients together.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and tasty casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and put in casserole baking dish.
Mix milk and soup; pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs, small chunks of oleo and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until nicely brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use with bananas, melon, strawberries, etc.

title: kiwi club(dose for 500 grs.)
directions: Peel the kiwis and cut in slices.
Sprinkle them with the lemon juice.
Blend the first and last slices (keep aside the rest of slices) of kiwi with the milk, yogurt and syrup.
Place the rest of slices at the inner side of the glass and pour little by little the blended mixture.
Put on top crushed ice and some gooseberries.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together 3 times.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: First, blend flour, baking soda and salt in one bowl.
In another bowl, blend peanut butter, eggs, white and brown sugars and shortening.
Blend until creamy, then add flour, baking soda and salt, little by little.
While adding, stir until all lumps are gone.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Simmer for one hour.
Serve over rice.

title: no bake strawberry bottom cheesecake
directions: Slice strawberries and set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually blend in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; set aside.
Spread a thin layer of glaze over bottom of crust.
Place sliced berries on glaze and cover with another layer of glaze.
Gently spoon cream cheese mixture over glazed berries.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers,
onions and tomatoes in bowl.
Combine and mix dressings
together.
Pour over vegetables and lightly mix.

title: quick and easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease bottom and sides well of an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish. Spread uncooked rice over bottom.
Arrange uncooked chicken breasts over rice.
Spread undiluted cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle oregano and basil over casserole.
Add water and cover.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: lorna's pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow baking pan.
Spread mustard on chops
and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Spread applesauce on top and
bake
approximately 3/4 hour at 350°.	Apple pie mix may be used in place of applesauce.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix crackers and melted margarine together and place on top. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and soda.
Blend in pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and fill with mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cover cake with icing.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Method 1:
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and set in a large pot or bowl.
Put chocolate coating, peanut butter and nuts in bowl. When thoroughly blended, add Rice Krispies, coconut and marshmallows.
Work fast so that the marshmallows are covered with the soft chocolate, but do not melt in any way. Pour into the greased pan and spread evenly and chill.
Turn out onto table under a towel and cut into squares.
Remember this will not keep too long after cutting because the marshmallows dry out.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, beating well after each. Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with sour cream, beating well after each. Add almond extract. Mix well. Spoon 1/3 mixture into a greased and floured tube pan. Spread 1/3 cranberry sauce over batter. Repeat layers twice more ending with cranberry sauce. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done. Let cool five minutes before removing from pan. Drizzle glaze over top.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Simmer for 2 hours or until most of the liquid is gone.
This is also a great dressing for sandwiches.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda until
blended.
Add 1/2 cup milk if batter is too thick.
Stir in nuts, oatmeal and chocolate.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet for 20 minutes or until done.

title: baked ziti(good meatless dish during lent.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 3-quart oblong baking dish.

title: grits with cheese
directions: Cook grits; remove from fire and add rest of ingredients.
Add egg whites last and pour in buttered dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Good with meats any time.

title: flan
directions: Mix all in blender.

title: chocolate eclair squares
directions: Line the bottom of a 13 x 9 baking pan with graham crackers; set aside. Combine chocolate pudding and 1 cup of milk; fold in half the whipped topping. Spread over graham crackers; add another layer of graham crackers on top. Repeat, using vanilla pudding in place of chocolate. Top with graham crackers. Blend remaining ingredients together. Pour over top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade ice cream peanut butter
directions: Beat egg with mixer real good.
Add canned milk, then Eagle Brand, vanilla, sugar, peanut butter and dash of salt.
Finish filling with regular milk up to freezer line.
Can add more sugar if you like.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and cook until tender.
Layer potatoes, cheese and onion in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Mix 1/2 can of water with mushroom soup.
Pour over mixture.
Top with paprika. Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Coarsely chop graham crackers.
Combine crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom
and up sides of 9-inch pan.
Combine whipped topping, pudding and sour cream.
Pour half of filling over crust.
Slice bananas on top.
Place remaining filling over bananas.
Finely chop pecans and sprinkle over top.
Sets immediately, but can be refrigerated to chill.

title: raspberry float
directions: Mix flour, butter, brown sugar and finely chopped nuts as for pie crust.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Beat two minutes or until well mixed.
Then add 3 more cups plain flour.
Knead down.
Let rise 1/2 size.
Put oil over top of dough.
Put cloth over bowl and place in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, roll out as many as needed, let rise and bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix well until dissolved.
Pour into popsicle holders and freeze.

title: christmas pie
directions: Thoroughly blend sugar, flour, gelatin and salt in a saucepan. Stir milk in gradually and cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Place pan in cold water. Cool mixture until it mounds when dropped from the spoon. Blend in vanilla and almond flavorings.
Whip the egg whites, cream of tartar and the 1/2 cup sugar.

Whip the whipping cream until it mounds. Add coconut and then add the rest of the mixture. Pile into baked 9-inch pie shell and chill for several hours. Serve with crushed strawberries or raspberries.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add sugar to well beaten egg.
Add shortening.
Pour over the mixture 1/2 cup boiling water, stirring thoroughly.
Add the dissolved yeast. Measure the salt with 3 cups of flour.
Mix sufficiently to get on the board and roll to your desired thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Brush tops with melted butter and fold over, not crowding.
Place in warm room and allow to rise 1 to 2 hours. Then place in preheated 400° oven.
Recipe can be doubled and the balance stored in refrigerator.
Can make a tea ring, clover leaf rolls and even a loaf of bread.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cool milk to lukewarm.
Add yeast and let stand until soft. Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add beaten egg and then yeast mixture.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Place in greased bowl and let rise 1 hour.
Divide dough into 2 balls.
Turn on lightly floured board.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into rounds with biscuit cutter.
Melt 1/3 cup butter.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Dip each round in butter and then sugar.
Stand each biscuit up in tube pan until full.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese log
directions: Blend together and shape into a roll or log.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: teriyaki burgers
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Then add the ground beef. Cook and spoon on buns.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies and 10 to 11 minutes for crispy cookies.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet and sour deer meatballs
directions: Put all ingredients except venison and pineapple chunks into square glass cake pan and cook in microwave for 7 minutes on High (100%), stirring it twice.
Form venison into balls and put into mixture.
When venison balls are put in, spoon sauce over them several times, cooking 7 more minutes and add drained pineapple. Heat 1 minute.
Taste best if they are cooked, left to stand overnight and heated just before serving.
Yields 24 venison balls.

title: j.b.'s chili "hot stuff"
directions: Brown and crumble hamburg or ground turkey.
Saute peppers and onions in 1 teaspoon oil, separately from meat, until tender.
Mix all ingredients (except jalapeno relish) in a pot or crock-pot and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add jalapeno relish, 1/4 jar at a time, to taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain the spinach well.
Mix all the remaining ingredients until blended.
Roll into walnut size balls and arrange close but not touching on cookie sheet.
Freeze until hard.
Store in freezer storage bag for up to one month.
To Serve:
Heat oven to 350°; bake 15 to 20 minutes until hot and firm enough to pick up.

title: ground turkey and spaghetti
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam.
Add ground turkey, onion and pepper; cook and stir over medium heat until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender, then drain.
Stir tomato sauce, mushrooms, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, garlic salt and pepper. Bring mixture to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti; omit oil and salt.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.

title: santa's whiskers cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Mix in cherries and pecans.
Form dough into two 8-inch rolls.
Roll in coconut to coat outside.
Wrap in wax paper. Chill.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased sheet.
Don't overbake.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: brown rice and lentil soup
directions: Combine vegetables, stock, tomatoes, lentils, rice and herbs. Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring occasionally until lentils and rice are tender, about 45 minutes.
Additional stock may be needed toward end of cooking.
Makes 8 servings. Freezes well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and prick squash with a fork.
Bake in microwave for 4 to 8 minutes, until tender.
Prepare like baked potato.

title: creme brulee
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine the beaten eggs, light cream, sugar and salt; cook and stir over medium heat about 10 minutes, or until custard coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat; cool at once by placing pan in the sink or a bowl of ice water, stirring 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into
a 1-quart casserole dish.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Press brown sugar through a sieve over the custard.
Set the casserole in a pan of ice cubes and cold water.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 1 or 2 minutes or until sugar turns golden brown and a bubbly crust forms.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan; crumble in raw hamburger.
Simmer 30 minutes without stirring.
(All cans should be of equal size.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Scramble sausage until brown.
Add onion, diced.
Add eggs to mixture and stir until done.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, eggs, cheese, eggs, cheese, etc. ending with cheese on top.
Brown under broiler.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 10 minutes; drain.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° until hot. When hot, top with can of onion rings.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: red potato salad
directions: In bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and celery seed.
In large bowl combine potatoes, onions, radishes, celery and eggs.
Add dressing and chill.

title: hot lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Mix thoroughly.
Slowly add boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve hot over pound cake or gingerbread.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and place in baking dish. Combine the remaining ingredients and sprinkle this topping over the potatoes. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: pork chops on rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil and brown chops on both sides. While chops are browning, combine remaining ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Top with browned chops and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until rice has absorbed all moisture.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons of batter into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes. Bake, uncovered.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Add both sugars and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Mix again.
Add half of chocolate chips and blend in.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (80 minutes in tube pan).

title: peach cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to wet mixture (gradually). Pour 1/2 of batter into loaf pan.
Slice peaches and lay over batter.
Add remaining batter.
Combine 1/3 cup of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over top of cake. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: reindeer cookies
directions: Use your favorite sugar cookie recipe or Pillsbury slice and bake cookies.
Roll out dough; cut into triangles with one side longer than the other two.
After baking, frost with frosting dyed with food coloring to be light brown.
Before frosting dries, press red hots in place for nose, 2 chocolate chips for eyes and 2 pretzels in place for antlers.
Perfect activity to share with children.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Melt butter.
Mix with brown sugar and 1 tablespoon pineapple juice in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Spread pineapple on bottom of pan.
Cream together shortening and sugar until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and 2/3 cup pineapple juice and mix at high speed until most lumps are gone. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Turn over on large plate.
Serve.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together until creamy.
Add the next 4 ingredients with the first 4, but mix them by hand.
Batter will be heavy.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put marshmallows on cake while hot, then spread frosting on top of cake.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Empty can of peach halves, syrup and all, into a saucepan.
Add cloves and allspice.
Then add brown sugar and vinegar.
Boil until the sugar dissolves.
Then simmer about 8 minutes.
Cool in the syrup.
(You may want to add less vinegar; suit to taste.)

title: krispie cheese buttons
directions: Cream cheese and margarine. Slowly, blend in flour. Stir in cereal and cayenne. Shape dough into one inch balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork that has been dipped in cold water. Bake 10 minutes in preheated 375° oven.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Stovetop Directions:
In a medium saucepan, heat the milk chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly until melted and smooth.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and walnuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a waxed paper-lined baking sheet.
Chill in the fridge for 15 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Combine in bowl, cream of mushroom soup, milk and salt; stir until blended.
Fold in cooked chicken, French green beans, chop suey vegetables, chopped onion and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until beans are tender.
Top with 13 1/2 ounce can of French onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Use juice from Bing cherries but not from pie cherries. Add enough water to make the jello; chill until partially set. Serve plain or with Cool Whip.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot; chop apple, then mix all together. Salt and pepper to personal taste.

title: grandma huffmaster's chicken
directions: Mix all liquids in baking dish.
Cut lemons in quarters. Squeeze into dish and drop lemons in dish.
Add chicken and marinate for 2 hours.
Place baking dish with chicken on top of stove burners and simmer until tender.
Broil or barbecue to complete.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in butter until the particles are mealy in appearance.
Add ice water and work dough until it is a soft ball.
Roll out and cut into 3-inch rounds, using a floured rim of a large glass.
In a saucepan, combine peaches, sugar, cornstarch, nutmeg and cinnamon; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.
Add lemon juice and butter, stirring until butter is melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Place mixture on half the circle of dough; fold empty half over and press the edges together.
Crimp with the tines of a fork.

title: easy-as-pie eclair cake
directions: Prepare both packages of instant pudding as package directs. Set aside.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix dessert topping with pudding.
Pour half the pudding-topping mixture over crackers.

title: tea cakes(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar; add egg yolks. Add milk and vanilla. Combine flour and baking powder. Add flour mixture to butter mixture. Shape into balls and flatten with fork on cookie sheet. Bake at 325°.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat; season with garlic powder, salt, cooked chopped onions with small amount of water.
Add meat and 2 tablespoons chili powder.
Simmer and add 2 small cans tomato sauce.

title: lentil soup
directions: Place lentils in cold water with ham bone and simmer 1 hour. Add vegetables to soup and simmer 1 hour more. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers and 1/2 of pudding/Cool Whip mixture.
Layer again and top with graham crackers.
Top with icing.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown beef with taco seasoning mix.
Drain fat.
Pat on the bottom of casserole.
Layer refried beans on top.
Add shredded cheese and diced onion.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with fresh, chunked tomatoes and serve with nacho chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: turnip slaw
directions: Combine ingredients for dressing and mix well.
Pour over the vegetables; toss to coat.
Refrigerate for several hours for best flavor.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beau monde vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill hours before serving with fresh vegetables.

title: sylvia's potato soup
directions: Peel and slice/dice potatoes into large pot.
Fry bacon; break into pieces and add to pot.
Dice onion into pot.
Add rest. Cook, uncovered, very slowly for 40 minutes or until done. Sprinkle parsley on each bowl as garnish.
Terrific winter supper!

title: diabetic potato cakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes in paper towels.
Squeeze out excess water and place potatoes in mixing bowl.
Peel and grate onion into potatoes.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix in flour and salt.
Heat oil in skillet.
Drop tablespoon of batter into skillet.
Fry on both sides until crisp and brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm with apple sauce.
Yields 36.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt and milk in saucepan; bring to boil.
Cook slowly, about 15 minutes, or until slightly thickened. Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Press into greased pan.
Let cool before cutting into squares.
Yields 1 pound.

title: "gram beat's" chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put in bottom of baking dish (9 x 11-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix cottage cheese, orange Jell-O and Cool Whip together.
Add drained fruit and mix.
Add chopped nuts and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: aunt helen's pink beet salad
directions: Mix lettuce, onion and beets.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten and salt to taste.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix well the buttermilk, soda, sugar and salt.
Pour over Karo syrup.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes, until it begins to boil.
Take off and beat until creamy.
Add nuts; continue beating until spreading consistency.
Spread on a buttered dish.
Cut immediately.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, jello and cornstarch and cook until thick. Cool and add strawberries to mixture.
Place in pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and freeze them on the cookie sheet, then place in freezer bags.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix the buttermilk with the instant pudding; stir well.
Break (do not crush) cookies into small pieces.
Drain mandarin oranges. Add Cool Whip and oranges to mixture.
Fold in cookies when just ready to serve.

title: aunt sarah's chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix in shortening, eggs and applesauce; blend.
Pour into greased 9 x 15-inch pan.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat Coca-Cola and add cream cheese, which has been creamed. Add Jell-O and stir, then add pineapple and nuts.
Put in 8 x 8-inch dish or mold.
It's nice and firm; molds nicely.

title: after dinner mint pie
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine (reserving 1/2 cup for topping). Press remaining crumbs in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill. Gradually add milk to Marshmallow Creme; mix until well blended. Add extract and food coloring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze until firm.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: sweet pickled peaches(try pickled peaches, they are good!)
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and spices together in a large kettle. Add peaches and cook on simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Place in sterile glass jars and seal.

title: graham cracker bar
directions: Place one layer whole graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan melt margarine, sugar, milk and egg.
Bring to full boil, stir constantly for one minute, then remove.
Add coconut, nuts and crumbs. Mix well. Pour over layer of crackers. Add another layer of whole crackers on top.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin, vanilla and nuts. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Optional to frost.

title: pep cocktail
directions: Invigorates mentality, builds up energy and physical strength. May be taken 2 or 3 times daily, 1 hour before meals.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Place in saucepan with 1/4 cup butter. Heat over medium until melted and smooth, stirring often.
Place vegetables in 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over and mix well.
Melt remaining butter.
Stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve at once.
Quick and tasty side dish!

title: oat topping
directions: Combine, mix and cook in skillet, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Dry on cookie sheet.
Store in covered container.
Serve as topping over fruit salad, rice dream or pudding.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Brown quickly in oil.
Drain on paper towel.
In skillet, place gravy mix, adding extra cup of water. Place steak, peppers and onion in gravy mix; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Prepare rice as directed on package.
Pour gravy and steak mix over rice.

title: cracker salad
directions: Chop the vegetables fine.
Crumble crackers coarsely.
Add the mayo; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: christmas balls
directions: Cream butter; mix flour and powdered sugar together and add to butter.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Shape into small balls and bake 45 minutes at 250°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
When cold, roll again in powdered sugar.

title: baked carrots julienne
directions: Melt margarine with lemon juice and salt.
Peel carrots and cut into small strips.
Arrange in layers in small baking dish, pouring part of margarine mixture over each layer.
Add water. Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until tender. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: sausage grits casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage; spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with the other ingredients mixed.
Stir together until cheese is melted.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with pimento strips and parsley.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.
Makes a large salad.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into melted margarine in frying pan.
Brown on both sides.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: christmas tarts
directions: Pour cream into a small bowl.
Add 1 cup flour (or a bit more).
Mix and turn out on pastry canvas.
(Dough will be soft and sticky.)
Roll out, adding more flour as necessary, and all little chunks of butter.
Double over; roll.
Add more butter; double over.
Roll.
Add more butter, etc. until butter is all used up.
Pick up dough and throw on the counter a few times (sounds silly, but it is necessary).
Chill dough.

title: best red cabbage
directions: Heat drippings in a skillet; add remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, over low heat; stir occasionally.
For crisp cabbage, cook for 15 minutes; for tender, cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Drain hearts and smash with fork.
Add everything else. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake in greased loaf pan or baking dish for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cutout cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Cut in margarine until like cornmeal.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Combine with flour and margarine mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll out dough; cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes (no longer than 8), then frost.

title: bacon-wiener roll-ups
directions: Slice hot dogs down the middle.
Slice cheese into strips and place in the middle of the hot dog.
Roll hot dog up in the bacon strips.
Bake at 375°, rotating hot dogs, until done.
Can be served on a bun or as a stand-alone meat.
Enjoy!

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water and onion.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Put through a sieve.
Add White Sauce.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and celery salt.
Heat to boiling.

title: peas and cheese salad
directions: Cook peas according to package until crisp-tender; drain.
In bowl, combine all ingredients except bacon.
Mix well.
Cover; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 7 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: scalloped clams
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: This is a good recipe for using those cucumbers which have gotten too large for regular dill pickles.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Boil raisins and water to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Add oil.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients; beat into raisin mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 17 to 18 minutes. Do not overbake.
Drizzle powdered sugar over cooled bars, if desired.

title: ice cream layer cake
directions: Note:
Dry cherries with paper towel or cloth so they won't bleed on Cool Whip.

title: knock you nakeds
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, pecans, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and melted butter.
Press half of batter into bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
In top of double boiler over simmering water, melt caramels with remaining 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour well mixed mixture over baked layer.
Cover with chocolate morsels. Pour remaining batter on top of morsels.
Bake for 18 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: westerner pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour, gradually to batter.
Add flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 4 minutes.
Invert pan.
Great plain or frosted.

title: 5 layer jello salad
directions: Dissolve first package of jello in 1 cup boiling water. Divide into 2 bowls.
In one bowl, add 1/3 cup sour cream.
In 2nd bowl, add 3 tablespoons of cold water.
Pour sour cream mixture in 9 x 13-inch glass pan first.
Let set, then put on clear layer. Repeat the same with each color.

title: strawberry (no bake) parfait cake
directions: Make small jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly
jelled.
Meanwhile, thaw and drain strawberries well.
Tear angel food cake into nickel size pieces.
Whip cream.
Whip the jello.
Fold the 2 together, then fold in strawberries.

title: okra salad
directions: Brown okra about 1/2 bag at a time.
Set aside to drain grease and cool.
In a large bowl mix okra, tomatoes and onion. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pear 'n raspberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch round cake pan. Combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk, egg and vanilla until well blended.
Spread mixture in pan; bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.
In saucepan over medium heat, combine raspberries, cornstarch and liqueur.
Cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Cool slightly; strain to remove seeds.
Melt remaining butter and sugar over medium heat.
Add pears; cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Arrange pear slices over top of cake; drizzle with half of the raspberry sauce.
Garnish with fresh raspberries; serve with remaining sauce on side.
This is too wonderful!!!
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and carrots until tender. Combine all ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Pour melted margarine over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together potatoes, cheese, sour cream, soup, onion, 1/3 cup melted margarine, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (3-quart size). Mix remaining 1/3 cup margarine with crushed corn flakes and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until hot and bubbly. Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion until transparent with water chestnuts and almonds in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix cooked chicken and rice with sauteed ingredients. Spread in a 10 x 15-inch pan. Top with chopped pimiento.
Mix mushroom soup with sour cream and spread over chicken.
May top with cheese or crumbs, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Allow dough to rise.
Then pinch off and form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in melted butter, then in the next 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle some nuts in bottom of pan and between layers and on top.
Place balls in a greased tube pan and pour any leftover butter and sugar over the top.
Let rise to 1/2-inch from top of pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before inverting onto plate.
Pull apart and eat!

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bread pan.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, beating well after each addition. Sift all-purpose flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add creamed mixture.
Fold in bananas, vanilla and pecans.
Pour mixture in pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter and add crawfish (crawfish should already be boiled).
Saute for 15 minutes.
Then add onions and seasonings. Cook on low fire, stirring when needed, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add flour to 5 ounces of water.
Mix well and add to smothered crawfish.
Stir for 3 minutes, then add water to create thickness desired.
Cook 5 minutes and season to taste.

title: louisiana pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until light, lemon colored, and frothy. Add sugar and syrup, finely chopped pecan meats (save enough halves to decorate top of pie), vanilla and salt.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt white chocolate in double boiler; stir in tidbits.
Let melt.
Place whole pecans on wax paper, then spoon 1 teaspoon mixture over pecans or chop pecans and put in melted mixture. Spoon on wax paper.
Place in refrigerator 4 to 6 minutes.

title: praline fingers
directions: Spread crackers on foil on cookie sheet. Mix sugar, butter and nuts; pour over crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Break, after cooling, into small pieces.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Remove the green skin from the rind and dice it into 1-inch cubes.
Soak rind overnight in salt water; drain well in the morning.
Make syrup of the other ingredients, bringing just to a boil.
Add the rind and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 pints.
The pickles can be canned.

title: liver pat(chicken liver chop)
directions: Put liver in a pot with enough water to cover it.
Add onion, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, and garlic.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium or medium low heat until liver is falling apart and most of the liquid is cooked out.
Drain and put into a food processor.
Add eggs and mayonnaise.
Blend until smooth.
You can add more salt, pepper, or mayonnaise to suit your taste.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Bring to a boil the orange Jell-O and pineapple.
Cool, but don't let it
start to jell.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill in oblong or square dish (glass).

title: peanut butter popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn warm in a 200° oven.
In heavy saucepan, bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil.
Continue boiling 30 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and beat in peanut butter and vanilla extract.
Pour over popcorn and stir.
Grease hands and shape into 16 balls.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix milk and biscuit mix into dough; roll out. Brush with melted butter. Mix 1 cup sugar and enough cinnamon to make sugar medium brown. Spread cinnamon sugar over dough. Roll up. Wrap in foil and put in refrigerator to cool. When cooled, slice and cook on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach dip(served with raw vegetables)
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Run under cold water for a few minutes.
Put into mixing bowl and add a heavy sprinkling of garlic powder; mix well.
Add garlic salt, onion, salt and pepper continuously mixing after a light sprinkling of each.
Add 4 ounces of mayonnaise and mix well.
Add soup mix.
Add another heavy sprinkling of garlic powder but do not mix.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Discard all grease, but 1 tablespoon. To bacon, add apple, cabbage, water, vinegar, salt and pepper. Cook with a top on pan for 45 minutes until tender.
Can be cooked in pressure cooker.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes and Parmesan cheese. Stir in potatoes.
Spread in ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: egg brunch
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bread evenly over bottom of pan.
Top with sausage.
Pour eggs over bread and sausage.
Pour margarine over mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix dressing in small bowl with the last 5 ingredients.
Mix dressing and macaroni together with hands.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: orange pineapple delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Cook macaroni in water.
Melt butter on low heat.
Cook pepper and onion.
Add corn, chili, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes. Stir in macaroni.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice in bowl, mixing well.
Fold in whipped topping, blending thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and chill for several hours before serving.

title: stuffed cabbage in the crock-pot
directions: Put hamburg, onion, cabbage and one can tomato sauce in crock-pot.
Then pour on top another can of tomato sauce with salt, pepper, garlic salt, allspice and brown sugar.
Then put Minute rice on top.
Cover and cook on high for 6 hours.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Cook peppers, onions, tomatoes and celery for 10 minutes in salt water.
Drain and combine with vinegar, sugar, flour and mustard.
Cook until thickened.
Add mayonnaise.

title: mom's zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Mix eggs, oil, zucchini and lemon peel in separate bowl. Add egg mixture to flour and mix together just until flour is moistened. Spread evenly in pans and bake 1 hour.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add molasses, beaten egg and milk. Add flour with baking soda, baking powder, salt and spice.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Melt shortening in baking pan.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange chicken in single layer in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut drop candy and chow mein noodles
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips; add peanuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Refrigerate.
You can use peanut butter chips instead of butterscotch.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in bananas, milk and extracts.
Add remaining ingredients and stir by hand.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased on bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 12 servings.

title: clam bake dip
directions: Simmer clams with its juice in lemon juice 10 minutes; set aside.
Melt margarine, then add dry ingredients.
Mix with clams and place in 7-inch Corning Ware pan.
Put paprika and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Form into small balls or drop from teaspoon and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: never fail chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Stir until sugar dissolves over moderate heat.
When mixture comes to rapid boil, boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool and then beat to spreading consistency.
Set in cold ice water and stir constantly to cool.
Spread on cake when it just starts to thicken.

title: chocolate loaf cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix in water and vanilla. Add mayonnaise.
Cover bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
Oil waxed paper.
Add batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with coconut and nuts.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese with margarine.
Add powdered sugar to this.
Pour over cake and bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour the two cups of rice into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a separate bowl mix the mushroom soup with the water, the can of mushrooms and minced onion.
Pour this mixture over the rice. Place pieces of chicken in an even layer on top of the rice.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: steak and noodle dinner
directions: Cut steak into 2-inch strips.
Brown steak, onion, pepper and garlic in Dutch oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add tomato sauce, water and sugar.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300° until steak is tender.
Put cooked, buttered noodles on a large platter and pour meat over the top.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and heat.
Add to jello.
Add all the fruit and mix well.
Add sugar and Coke and mix well.
Set in the refrigerator until jelled.

title: strawberry layer jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries and refrigerate.
Mix sugar, butter and crushed pretzels.
Pat pretzel mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Add partially set jello on cooled crust.
After jello is set, add the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip, which has been mixed together.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Beat shortening and 2/3 cup of sugar in bowl until smooth and creamy.
Stir in egg and molasses.
Combine cereal, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves in separate bowl.
Add to sugar mixture, mixing well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned. Let stand 1 minute before removing to racks to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: onkers
directions: Work cheese and flour together until crumbly.
Add butter; mix well with fork.
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each (surprise). Shape into ball.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sauteed scallops with garlic and tomatoes
directions: Roll scallops in flour.
In skillet, heat oil and butter; cook scallops 3 to 5 minutes over medium heat, shaking pan to turn scallops.
Add salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and cook briefly until soft, then add parsley.
Toss scallops to coat.
Can serve with rice.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Mix gelatin in hot water until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1-quart mold; chill until firm.

title: crystal garden
directions: Mix the water, bluing, salt and ammonia together and stir well.
Place the charcoal in a soup bowl.
Put bowl in a large dish.
Now pour solution over charcoal and put bowl where it won't be disturbed.
You can color your garden by putting ink or food coloring in the bowl.
In a few hours, the first crystals will form and in a few days, a wonderful crystal garden will fill the bowl.

title: microwaving cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage and water in large bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 5 minutes on High to soften.
Mix ground beef, rice, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons soup. Divide among cabbage leaves.
Fold in sides.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Place cabbage rolls, seam side down, in 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
